skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "7d70ba33-0822-4dcb-914b-68c497f57f3f", "value": "An arch with jambs that do not stand at an angle of ninety degrees to its face."}
{"id": "164e4076-6f19-4cd0-a0a0-1803f786a89e", "value": "An arch which is half an ellipse."}
{"id": "19e812f2-3c99-4270-a218-eccc88d77a13", "value": "An arch where vertical piers raise the springing line."}
{"id": "330daf88-6f0d-44ca-92fa-18108cc1659a", "value": "An arch produced by two curves, usually each with a radius equal to the span, which meet at a point."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "ab64492b-64d2-4637-915c-ea3f6c34ee73", "value": "FISH Components"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "5e843fdb-4cb8-40b0-a120-4fa5733c811c", "value": "Terminology covering divisions and structural elements of a building or monument"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "f88b9e52-592f-4414-9ca2-6a1cd5f2e6ef", "value": "An opening in a structure which is arched."}
{"id": "9b510250-1611-4830-bb46-897ab13824a5", "value": "An arch which has a larger radius on the front face of a wall than on the back."}
{"id": "c4e81936-2a66-4a33-9cb8-02498e2f5e9c", "value": "The lower, or inner, curve of an arch"}
{"id": "98dd167e-72c4-41c4-affe-f3e290902a31", "value": "An arch whose height is equal to its span."}
{"id": "40809a68-71a8-4782-9cd4-40035675eb92", "value": "An arch consisting of a segment of a circle connected to other segments with smaller radii."}

{"id": "e879ccb9-2955-4275-ab14-6c4f2022ebc2", "value": "A pointed arch which, on a plan, is shown to be constructed around four arcs: two centred below and two centred upon the springing line, which is the level at which the vertical sides of the arch begin to curve."}
{"id": "85ff6abf-cb57-42f1-862e-b6533f493ca4", "value": "An arch which is formed by keystones but is flat like a lintel"}
{"id": "ba96227e-eeb7-45b7-954c-04c455c1331e", "value": "One or more arches built across an angle between two walls to support a polygonal or circular structure."}
{"id": "23cb5765-f3e1-4f76-b090-b42af1bb8e15", "value": "An arch associated with the portion of the stage between the curtain and the orchestra."}
{"id": "c0e8131f-cb4d-40b1-9750-799bcadee0ed", "value": "An arch at the liturgical east of the nave, carrying a gabled wall above, separating nave from chancel."}
{"id": "7331b7db-9e6c-4efc-a735-14c1dfec326d", "value": "A flat arch or lintel with quadrants on the corbels rising from the jambs."}
{"id": "5999e56f-f57b-4cc5-b286-aad1617b8c1d", "value": "The outer curve of an arch or vault."}
{"id": "7154664d-e7cf-4f60-8175-6649866f3359", "value": "A depressed arch formed around three arcs: two struck from the springing line with one centrally placed arc struck from below it."}
{"id": "b331b475-f1ba-4d53-9d4c-fe37d07d9d9f", "value": "A wedge shaped brick used to construct arches."}
{"id": "dbe1295e-f312-4016-b5ba-57f9b393b301", "value": "A temporary support placed under a vault or arch to support them during construction."}
{"id": "54dd87fd-2f9e-4a65-ad16-f1bb853eaa80", "value": "An arch built by corbelling or cantilevering in from both sides with horizontal joints."}
{"id": "b4eeceab-f77a-4bdc-ba3b-477c6c2ada92", "value": "An arch of the Tuscan Order."}
{"id": "20046cb0-d3e2-4dae-aaa2-fbb93d9d9ff4", "value": "An arch built into a wall above another arch or lintel to relieve it of some of the weight of the structure above."}
{"id": "5702c9bf-d850-404a-8108-2b89308ac27c", "value": "An arch formed around two arcs whose radii are each equal to the span of the arch."}
{"id": "d4a89c30-150c-477b-b798-ce0fac13ef70", "value": "An arch whose purpose is to arrest or prevent structural movement in a building."}

{"id": "aa4e3af2-ceb0-41a9-8e8b-f5e311235335", "value": "A curved construction, spanning an opening, formed from wedge-shaped blocks supported by mutual pressure; they can also be formed from moulded concrete and cast metal."}
{"id": "67522397-6898-44eb-b2ac-2318f30c15a3", "value": "An arch, either pointed or round, which broadens above the springing line, creating a horseshoe shape."}
{"id": "98a49efb-e3c4-43d3-a1a7-ec091c7e389a", "value": "An arch made up of part of a circle, the centre of which is below its springing line."}
{"id": "02267cc1-6f92-4626-a957-a26b37873377", "value": "The band or block from which the springing of an arch occurs."}
{"id": "f9a13647-b8ae-4660-bcd2-9349b99822fc", "value": "The part of a rib or arch visible below the general surface of the vault."}
{"id": "bea3a4e3-4873-4402-9fa8-d2a00403572f", "value": "A room in a public house, hotel, club etc. containing a bar from which alcoholic drinks are served."}
{"id": "f4beaa85-98ff-44d6-8da7-7adfe2e03f74", "value": "A counter from which beverages are served in a bar room."}
{"id": "1bc894bc-21b1-4215-950a-30bf3323a31b", "value": "A wholly or partially underground chamber, often beneath a chancel, equipped for religious services and usually containing tombs."}
{"id": "c83c2222-e194-4aad-b202-c8804c7ceb9a", "value": "A room for private work, reading etc."}
{"id": "ccfd9d44-f54b-4eb5-9ef6-d9f7ca2f6f43", "value": "A room for detention and imprisonment within a prison."}
{"id": "276a7345-6401-4c9d-bad8-534ec0b775f0", "value": "The undressing room in a bath house or similar."}

{"id": "84899bbb-be78-4ac3-86c7-6b30c922ef78", "value": "An apartment for the use of people of high status, often the owner of the building. Also a room adjoining, or close to, a hall and used as a drawing room or venue for private functions."}
{"id": "e1c99fda-7964-4694-9eac-fc89a14fd314", "value": "A room where usually materials or consumables are processed into tools or meal, for example in a workshop or mill."}
{"id": "a5f91bee-961b-4fbb-a2be-f5851b0ae880", "value": "A room, within a building or institution, equipped for conducting scientific experiments or research."}
{"id": "16831826-eabc-4c50-b391-4b38bd681a08", "value": "A room in which domestic appliances and facilities for cleaning are stored."}
{"id": "267d12d2-cb93-40f8-b78f-aef13cd15a44", "value": "A room or group of rooms in a building."}
{"id": "0518ae92-2631-4a05-915d-279cf543a6db", "value": "Room in a building or complex in which the master of an establishment, such as a workhouse or a school, is accommodated."}
{"id": "3b3836f6-130b-4bf9-b23a-3eaf0cf9b8b8", "value": "An area of several rooms in a medieval house or building. Probably for domestic use."}
{"id": "dc85c22f-b484-4915-975a-542d09d4077d", "value": "A concealed passage or room for the purpose of hiding and protecting a (Roman Catholic) priest during times of religious persecution."}
{"id": "00bd9155-81f1-472d-b995-c5b5efe335c6", "value": "The warm room in a Roman baths."}
{"id": "cd3bef3d-7c42-4467-ac55-971085e3ed6e", "value": "A small room used as a study for the preservation of papers etc. Generally use for any small room appended to a larger one."}
{"id": "78be1736-aeab-4267-90a7-3087d4a5d8d4", "value": "A room in which servants slept."}
{"id": "c1605f3c-a92e-42e0-a5ad-64fb817af64b", "value": "A treasury, often the bursar's room in a college or university."}
{"id": "df0848ae-69fc-44b0-96be-9cf2bf06f2ee", "value": "A first-floor chamber, often serving as a parlour, bedchamber or private room, in a medieval house. Also a loft, rood-loft or garret."}
{"id": "1d0d029f-1e81-4661-b506-dd0680bd3266", "value": "A workroom or apartment, often with a north-light, used for the creation of artwork by painters, sculptors etc."}
{"id": "ec150242-151b-4206-9849-d319b71cc306", "value": "A long room for recreation, often on an upper floor."}

{"id": "1f5f76f2-b42d-404f-a360-7ff4c181232f", "value": "A large, high-ceilinged room, usually in a great house or palace, serving as a principal reception room; also a room used by the public for a specific purpose; or a drawing room in a house."}
{"id": "76b35132-0759-4519-b7f3-665806704699", "value": "A room intended for the pursuit of recreational activities."}
{"id": "54ae3502-770f-481b-b2b0-d847b5970115", "value": "A room in a monastery used by monks or nuns as a day room."}
{"id": "ee21fc7f-8086-4ae3-845a-bba0157217f8", "value": "A chamber built into a wall in a defensive structure."}
{"id": "ff4321cd-c31f-4ac5-ae2b-b80d4fa5b1c4", "value": "A room usually set aside for the provision of materials used in a household."}
{"id": "e5088eae-b6a7-4194-90d5-3afa40962393", "value": "A small room communicating with one or more apartments."}
{"id": "367dd6d2-d4b5-45ff-b3b1-b490bf69acc4", "value": "A room used for sleeping or resting in. Use more specific term."}
{"id": "21fdb1f2-ea9d-434a-bcd0-af460fbbf3db", "value": "The hot room in a Roman baths."}
{"id": "e3ca0730-44bc-4916-bbd9-cd703cf2b392", "value": "A room equipped for the care of babies and young children."}
{"id": "bae054c4-c9ee-4294-83d0-17f7f82113fe", "value": "A room in which cloaks, coats, hats etc may be left and often including coathooks, hat boxes and similar fixtures and fittings."}
{"id": "456f980c-b446-44eb-a1f8-2445104bbfb1", "value": "The hall before a great hall."}
{"id": "55b65c76-e052-418b-b86f-67983c545ba3", "value": "A room for servants, particularly where they would eat."}
{"id": "9cae8598-c12b-43b7-97cb-d24738e5d882", "value": "A suite of rooms."}
{"id": "a32551a4-21c8-46ce-adbc-98c5154fe9d2", "value": "A room for holding receptions particularly balls."}
{"id": "b3012432-5d6a-496a-8438-ca3ba15d1801", "value": "A room for temporary imprisonment and detention at a Police Station."}
{"id": "dbb89ad7-6453-431f-8c9e-29602d399f79", "value": "Originally, the inner sanctuary of a Greek temple from where the oracle was delivered. Now used for any private chamber or sanctuary."}
{"id": "44fb5f30-ff1e-4443-b1ec-6875b3d8ab89", "value": "A small room off a bedroom, usually in eighteenth century houses, in which a person would have their wig powdered."}
{"id": "06157537-dd21-48f2-abcb-95a13bff5fb2", "value": "A ticket booth in a theatre or cinema."}
{"id": "89e6a47f-bb36-44ae-bf64-8c4ef9f70f7c", "value": "A place set apart to contain books for reading, study or reference."}
{"id": "999df22a-a228-4e97-a1a8-6931bc4af443", "value": "A room decorated, and furnished, in the style of the Chinese."}

{"id": "77fdb9ec-6a9b-42fa-8cab-156c1ffc4382", "value": "A room, particularly in a house or theatre, intended for dressing or changing one's clothes and furnished with wardrobes, dressing tables and other facilities for the application of make-up, styling of hair etc."}
{"id": "5fe8fbde-5558-465a-92a5-a0ea0346d007", "value": "A room or group of rooms for healing the sick. Where it is a monument use the Thesaurus of Monument Types."}

{"id": "1a397481-1389-49d0-973c-bb398bb67921", "value": "The tower, generally attached to a church or other building but sometimes separate, where bells are hung and from which sound is emitted. Also applied to the upper chamber where bells are hung, or the wooden structure supporting them."}
{"id": "dd3d34db-c835-48aa-b8d4-4465f9e5ba1f", "value": "An open area within a bank where financial transactions take place."}
{"id": "29ecc66d-ce9e-4235-9842-55b8e9172bf7", "value": "A communal sleeping room in medieval houses for male servants."}
{"id": "e8c66c0c-6ac6-4915-9424-dc07ff41c7f0", "value": "A room, or part of a kitchen, for the cleaning and storage of kitchen utensils."}
{"id": "f4c33c12-4437-4deb-83b2-843249460d4d", "value": "A room before a larger room which is often used as a waiting room."}
{"id": "ba05c257-a3d7-47e4-9fee-d8a05ab80c33", "value": "Room in a building or complex, such as a workhouse, in which work is carried out."}
{"id": "c05b647c-4c87-4298-8f0b-833ff492b00c", "value": "A room in which actions are checked, verified and approved."}
{"id": "ebca110b-2059-4c53-96b5-b3f5ff0d3828", "value": "An enclosed compartment within a building intended for a purpose other than as a thoroughfare."}
{"id": "337e6881-cfcf-485c-8f96-2c5c6bbd339d", "value": "A room or hall designed for an audience to listen and view, as in a theatre, concert hall, lecture hall etc.."}
{"id": "43454b0d-9d1b-4808-82aa-0add0d665bed", "value": "A room intended for, and usually equipped to aid, the performance of ablutions."}
{"id": "99792246-8e18-4075-8d2a-d93e7befdf37", "value": "A room within a school, private house or institution used for lessons."}
{"id": "6cd6c958-b00b-4d6f-9050-1bff49cda562", "value": "A room, usually at ground level or below, housing the tank in which water is heated as part of a building's heating system."}
{"id": "842081f2-7860-4370-9f41-348fbe9011c5", "value": "A room set aside for the initial treatment of injuries sustained for example in public amenities such as lidos."}
{"id": "ea962227-4901-4ce7-9c4d-85754d90f6ec", "value": "A room within a church or cathedral in which holy relics were kept."}
{"id": "117bd89a-2bb8-4ef9-9b49-8f5ba0869211", "value": "A room for higher-ranking servants."}

{"id": "e3b0f32c-c98f-4907-96a9-e0e489000ac2", "value": "Term used to indicate the basic unit of accommodation in the plan of a building. It does not necessarily relate to the structural divisions within a building."}
{"id": "cf2aedb5-fb63-4dc8-a0ff-d11de7a8e275", "value": "A room intended, and often furnished accordingly, as a venue for the holding of meetings."}
{"id": "4eeb9767-2e24-4362-a0f9-aa6c53c634c0", "value": "A recess or chamber near the altar which holds a relic. A feature of medieval churches."}
{"id": "31a54cdc-fdb1-47d9-87d6-a2c980c0fb8d", "value": "The part of a house frequented by servants when not performing their duties."}
{"id": "7795d751-dfc2-4b65-a657-0635e27fb7bb", "value": "A room over the vestry of a church, often thought to have been where anchorets lived."}

{"id": "d1d66632-4f5e-4eba-8363-d596aa140cb2", "value": "A room provided for the use of people waiting for a service, such as a train or bus service, or to see an individual such as a doctor or a dentist. When a dedicated structure, see Thesaurus of Monument Types."}
{"id": "459800ce-4f06-4e90-a336-d7745ed53fa2", "value": "A private chamber usually in a Royal residence."}
{"id": "216a2aaa-d91e-4a2f-8d76-c5e8ecc34486", "value": "A room that serves as a combined living-room, kitchen and workshop."}
{"id": "c08428e7-fb94-4f03-8abd-bf84ea29a637", "value": "A room containing one or more thrones."}

{"id": "5f4cc662-9cd3-4a2d-8cbb-82288dfae182", "value": "A room within a building, such as a shop or leisure complex,sometimes equipped with cubicles or screens to allow a degree of privacy, where clothing can be tried on or changed."}
{"id": "dd9f4441-c5bb-495b-9a43-cfc0c6a98dc0", "value": "The principal room in early houses, which occupies the entire height of the building."}
{"id": "3dc81d8d-3e5d-4e18-9daf-13e8ad8a92a5", "value": "A room set aside for the storage of goods or valuables. Use more specific term where known."}
{"id": "986e75cf-e680-4e7a-82f4-3c0a2fe0d6ff", "value": "A room within a building or complex, such as a workhouse, used for purifying objects with smoke."}
{"id": "c5d719a4-dbb1-459c-8c11-d75f18c0df96", "value": "A room in a monastery from which alms were distributed; or the residence of an almoner."}
{"id": "b827d450-3fc6-466c-914e-33cebe499352", "value": "The cold room in a Roman baths."}
{"id": "bf693796-c25c-4140-84fb-41edc5c2f00a", "value": "A room dedicated to the drawing or letting of blood, a procedure once thought to possess medicinal properties."}
{"id": "e5fde400-fc77-48d0-a6f7-97b7a91c9d52", "value": "A room frequently in a military building where sentries guard and protect the premises."}
{"id": "b8e9f61c-ff48-4224-8596-06c8dea65900", "value": "A room in a church to receive the congregation's offerings."}
{"id": "7f627f21-c11d-44fb-a58f-75ba51cb6ccd", "value": "A room for washing and cleaning linen."}
{"id": "998da49e-fbf8-4ca4-8df6-c83fb09a973b", "value": "A room where letters and parcels are sorted prior to dispatch"}
{"id": "6f684dc2-1abd-43c2-87cb-7bf9c5f10004", "value": "A room which contains, wholly or partly, a staircase."}
{"id": "ec457658-24f8-447c-a3d3-be1f92c7e832", "value": "A room, furnished with tables and chairs, where meals and refreshments are served and consumed."}
{"id": "d445b8bb-e736-49a6-a7b4-87c8ac433964", "value": "A room or group of rooms usually reserved for use by the monarchy or government."}
{"id": "bbef7376-5bd6-44da-ba05-409bd1ed54a6", "value": "A room in a house, hotel, business premises etc. where guests or visitors are received."}
{"id": "cd6524ff-bfc4-44ec-812c-151efa2e685c", "value": "A room in a church where vestments and sacred vessels are stored."}
{"id": "aec7db74-331c-4414-8bb4-90b8bc06b64a", "value": "A room set aside within a building where social and other functions such as parties, presentations and meetings can be held."}
{"id": "0b093918-3444-403d-9b3d-964f9826973e", "value": "A room in which food is prepared."}
{"id": "5300ab95-85fd-4502-b379-6daec94e3e01", "value": "A room used in a church to store vestments and for the clergy to dress in."}
{"id": "6fb36239-26a9-4448-b890-6be8a1889a49", "value": "A room in which commercial or administrative activities are carried out."}
{"id": "763c8039-5237-4a64-8841-7ee7c855f6bc", "value": "Room within a building or complex used by a porter."}
{"id": "760c57b2-4be5-4efd-b322-ce2e193405b3", "value": "A chamber for the incarceration of one or more prisoners."}
{"id": "976dc5ff-eb2f-416d-bf9c-3ec4d19d2301", "value": "A projecting wall or structure, such as a parapet or battlement, supported by a series of corbels."}
{"id": "7c311dab-4870-462c-ad3b-229200989798", "value": "A cantilevered block projecting from the face of a wall and supporting a structure such as a parapet, beam or arch."}
{"id": "9c1b48fd-074e-4378-98d5-7245edd1991a", "value": "A machine tool for producing flat surfaces and slots on small work pieces by cutting away surplus material."}

{"id": "05f92233-93f3-4f30-a429-d8e4e3faa202", "value": "A machine tool similar in general appearance to a shaping machine but in which the head or ram carrying the cutting tool moves in a vertical plane."}
{"id": "8207c4e0-858a-4c28-8e06-f03d58298629", "value": "An H-sectioned strip of lead used to hold panes of glass in position in stained-glass windows or other leaded lights."}
{"id": "d119a91c-31f2-4222-b7ae-39b2752c034e", "value": "A tall, narrow window with a pointed arched head."}
{"id": "b5156051-4a6c-47d1-8bee-9c229d4e2acf", "value": "A small square or lozenge-shaped pane of glass as used in a leaded light."}
{"id": "41b83dc0-898b-4cc9-aa8c-9d2e6eed2ddd", "value": "A window with three openings, the central light being arched and wider than those flanking it."}
{"id": "01a53a65-cb43-4279-b960-144a0d0ea716", "value": "An oval window placed with its long axis horizontal. The term is often applied to similar round windows."}
{"id": "37632fb6-eb1d-4b6a-916d-5dac9c70c15b", "value": "A window set within a curved projection from the face of a wall."}
{"id": "a28b4337-b008-4bc3-8636-94103d022c7c", "value": "A circular or oval window or panel. Also the circular opening at the top of a dome."}
{"id": "45f8ad48-c3fd-4d2a-876c-f943120a790e", "value": "A bay window, supported by corbelling, cills or brackets, projecting from an upper storey of a building."}
{"id": "88d78db0-bf16-4a73-803a-1075831f79cb", "value": "A window which has its head beam decorated with elements of tracery."}
{"id": "e393edd2-b87b-47c7-aa64-e1ef29c744a5", "value": "The framing of a door or window with two columns piers or pilasters which support a lintel,entablature etc."}
{"id": "37a222f8-518e-47da-9e9c-b3c6fcea1cf8", "value": "A window that forms a projection from the body of a building, extending down to ground level, forming a bay in the wall's interior."}
{"id": "354bcae5-88f4-4089-a732-14673c56c352", "value": "A window divided into lights by mullions."}
{"id": "95341a5c-ad70-4679-aa7b-925630637f5a", "value": "An opening in a wall, roof, door, etc to allow light to enter. Usually used to include all component parts."}
{"id": "1e45f51b-e680-41e5-b4db-f1f47c1bd7a5", "value": "A window where the sash is hung vertically and the window opens outwards or inwards."}
{"id": "0b501ed9-d444-486a-b4e8-7d6b0cdca294", "value": "A small window placed to cast light upon a fireplace."}
{"id": "a79f218d-730a-49ea-83e0-0e0c88a0d2d7", "value": "A vertical iron bar fixed within a window opening to support a leaded light."}
{"id": "f36579f9-b625-433e-8291-0908c48274c3", "value": "A window that is lower than others in the chancel side wall."}
{"id": "5bc10ad3-726c-47cf-a33d-b2af54137a9a", "value": "A window with a single mullion and a single transom."}
{"id": "a6bc3597-bfb1-4835-91c7-7af2182643ab", "value": "A window either in the shape of a four leaf clover or circular with four foils enclosed."}
{"id": "29265329-a107-4d9b-b209-b01e7bf6a944", "value": "A shaped or decorated raised panel below the sill of a window or a niche."}
{"id": "385e8ae8-9db0-4a52-ada4-10599a807555", "value": "A semi-circular window, often decorated and with its glazing bars radiating like the ribs of an opened fan, set above a door."}
{"id": "36b33923-cb0e-45ef-b26e-9563723c57c1", "value": "A section of a window between mullions; thus for example a three-light window."}
{"id": "afe1a72f-421d-4daa-a056-83b6c386fb60", "value": "A lintel over a window."}
{"id": "79a90508-9147-4649-a8ab-360fd3ceab2c", "value": "A window with a frame for holding the glass, capable of being raised and lowered in vertical grooves."}
{"id": "86750d1d-aece-4509-b9dc-022b6ecc120c", "value": "A window usually spanning the full width of the north side of a roof allowing the maximum amount of direct and indirect light to enter."}
{"id": "e306e625-42dd-4eba-85ef-9ac5e80d41ad", "value": "A projecting vertical window in the sloping roof of a house."}
{"id": "a605383d-f8ab-4c10-9cc3-ba6ca510444a", "value": "A window cut through a single slab of timber or stone."}
{"id": "8608ef96-79a1-4cfb-8fa9-e396211f8723", "value": "A window in a spire, often in the form of a dormer."}
{"id": "d9adcfd5-46dd-41fc-a848-a1045d557b38", "value": "A circular window with tracery or shafts radiating from the centre."}
{"id": "c838b1c2-d24a-4e88-89f8-0f635b94488d", "value": "One of a set of windows placed vertically and linked either decoratively or by aprons extending to the lintel below."}
{"id": "69072892-1605-4881-9a72-db5f21158b69", "value": "A circular window containing tracery."}
{"id": "5751a23b-1baf-4ebc-8648-1a09e2262db7", "value": "A moulded bar or baton dividing the panes of glass within a window light."}
{"id": "90d48106-553d-4527-9c53-7b8a439d25cf", "value": "A horizontal iron bar set in a window opening to which a leaded light is fixed."}
{"id": "f5401c10-21c4-4c0e-b191-0e2363d3c5a6", "value": "A window in the form of a three-leafed clover."}
{"id": "0b2de047-cd13-493f-b6d5-56b7de126937", "value": "A high tower, attached to or detached from a building such as a church, with a belfry stage containing bells."}
{"id": "fe5c0cf3-5da7-4e9f-a9d3-31858a900593", "value": "A stage in a church tower where bell ringers stand."}
{"id": "02bf127c-12c2-4103-8cd7-6e80ca3c4fd9", "value": "The intersection and space between the nave, chancel and transepts in a cruciform church."}

{"id": "cdbeed3c-4fa4-4dda-a710-dba22f6f1a44", "value": "A small structure, often polygonal or circular, on top of a roof, dome, tower etc. featuring apertures to light or ventilate the building it adorns."}

{"id": "dd6bb750-6534-43b5-b8c3-01364ae98bfa", "value": "A tower which rises above the space at the intersection of the nave, chancel and transepts of a church. Usually pierced by windows to provide light directly to the area below."}
{"id": "341610e7-dce2-48df-af33-dd8272098dbc", "value": "The vertical face of a step."}
{"id": "c35c2d9e-4303-44dd-949a-f85ca26dac70", "value": "A flight of steps leading from one level to another."}
{"id": "546691b6-c890-48b8-9f45-ae3c3ec51fa7", "value": "The horizontal surface of a step or stair."}
{"id": "75a1070a-f121-49c3-bd5e-7cbb58f572d8", "value": "A decorative S-shaped moulding, usually placed at the top of a cornice, with a convex lower half and a concave upper half."}
{"id": "1bddaf90-2f42-43b5-a4c1-331dcc6183c3", "value": "A decorative form consisting of two upright S-shaped curves positioned opposite one another with their concave sections placed at the top."}
{"id": "f7cfe7c8-8263-4608-adf1-70af916081f6", "value": "A decorative moulding depicting an animal or bird head with a tongue or beak that overlaps the moulding set below it."}

{"id": "8a06f05d-e3f3-4dc4-b87c-f05f07957ac4", "value": "A decorative moulding depicting an animal or bird head, similar to a beak head moulding but with a shorter, cone-like tongue or beak overlapping the moulding set beneath it."}
{"id": "b17f4cb7-f477-49e4-8021-e6028f5e6e19", "value": "An enclosure or niche in a library or cloister used for study."}

{"id": "61016d15-c8a6-4fb7-b287-a1bb101d850b", "value": "A semicircular niche in the wall of a mosque used to indicate the Qiblah - the direction to be faced during prayers. Qiblah is set as the direction of the Kaaba in Mecca."}
{"id": "731af40d-10a3-47fe-818d-223f22b42241", "value": "A semicircular niche or recess in a wall."}
{"id": "f3edd8bd-c194-47a6-9798-9e4283cbb232", "value": "In churches a niche, or shelf, within or beside a piscina, or a table for the sacramental elements and vessels. (Source: Pevsner Glossary)"}
{"id": "4b1e72c4-231c-4c24-a5ed-5b16ddfc9904", "value": "A shallow, ornamental recess, often arched and semicircular in plan, set in a wall or pier and usually containing a statue or ornament."}
{"id": "87765efe-bfb0-4b2c-a3cc-4e45f20bed0a", "value": "A niche in the corner of a structure."}
{"id": "0c38130a-4be3-47e5-83b7-19ba26f77fd0", "value": "An external wall cladding consisting of overlapping horizontal boards."}
{"id": "00120932-be9f-46e4-9f90-85f3882cac06", "value": "A piece of cladding in the form of a length of timber fixed horizontally to the building."}
{"id": "739a3caf-98a4-4b8e-bbb0-502740d9dfbb", "value": "A mullion of square section set diagonally."}
{"id": "83a2ed59-cc6d-4518-a343-fcfa2a91a3b5", "value": "A horizontal member dividing a window into two or more lights."}

{"id": "46b879aa-b5fb-43f6-9c27-b42eb13b2e2b", "value": "A mullion which divides a window with four or more lights and is larger than the mullions either side of it, often sharing the dimensions of the frame?s members."}
{"id": "9ae08ea4-94cf-47c2-a432-7ebefdc95084", "value": "A vertical member dividing a window into two or more lights."}
{"id": "c7a39836-41fe-4551-9821-d89e82248bc8", "value": "An upright framing member, or mullion, that separates two panels, such as in a panelled door or a window."}
{"id": "a2d578bc-a1f1-437f-a40d-30aab63f90cd", "value": "The top stone in a gable end."}
{"id": "62161d71-01c9-4bfb-854e-d2e94835a2e0", "value": "The part of the wall that supports a pitched roof at the end of the roof."}
{"id": "b4bb0b63-fb8f-4206-a0d4-c35cf8caf1be", "value": "A timber placed horizontally in a cob or stone wall to support the foot of a post or cruck blade."}
{"id": "baf71973-993f-491f-8542-ccc97968edcb", "value": "A stone block set into a wall to support a truss or beam."}

{"id": "5a21fd20-99d3-4db8-9bc4-106202df1eea", "value": "The post at the centre of a winding staircase from which the steps radiate; or the post, supporting the handrail and string, at the angle of a square staircase."}
{"id": "979a3287-9948-4962-ba67-630b637a961a", "value": "A staircase where the vertical members are placed at the ends of flights to support the strings, handrails, trimmers and bearers."}
{"id": "17ef4587-4718-4df9-9767-1245693f412b", "value": "The lower area of a interior wall between the skirting board and the dado rail"}

{"id": "530d2c2e-c453-4680-a8c9-449f732059e3", "value": "A wall-mounted moulding defining the upper edge of the dado, intended to protect the wall's surface from damage caused by chairs being pushed against it."}
{"id": "594f3405-cde2-4120-848c-c37cc7d58877", "value": "A circular moulding."}
{"id": "38de04ba-9135-4fab-a0f3-0302a83abfab", "value": "A narrow timber board or moulding lining the base of an interior wall as a finish between it and and the floor."}
{"id": "031f80dd-03df-47cf-9980-d53f2fd701ef", "value": "A decorative moulding in the form of a chain."}
{"id": "6b1f345c-3b8c-4503-8b09-582162aa7b5f", "value": "A decorative moulding featuring a series of small, projecting, dome-like shapes each resembling a halved nutmeg."}
{"id": "017cb4b0-170e-4857-a586-fb5c2a07c973", "value": "A decorative style on a block or band from which an arch springs."}
{"id": "3f2d1318-4029-4630-ba4d-ebe683c500b2", "value": "A large, convex moulding, sometimes ornamented, set at the base of a column and above its plinth."}
{"id": "368f1073-9cf9-4852-a824-6eae4c85265e", "value": "A moulding on the neck of a column."}
{"id": "4c2f6525-2709-407a-8bf2-26271d823914", "value": "A three-dimensional decorative ornamentation composed of a series of Vs forming a zigzag."}
{"id": "aebac3e1-85da-47dc-bce5-94ad1eff202f", "value": "A curved moulding with a sharp edge running along its centre. So named as its profile resembles the keel of a ship."}
{"id": "6eeadcf4-66f8-4860-b615-b8417bf39d0e", "value": "A convex, finger-like moulding, usually applied in a series to form a pattern of ridges."}
{"id": "27d7ff4f-c831-4256-8cc7-f8a45c769b63", "value": "A decorative moulding in a diamond shape."}
{"id": "7a3e362a-fd17-4b78-b14e-27eb5f722d8a", "value": "A deeply concaved moulding, with a projecting lower edge, that sits at the base of a column between two torus mouldings."}
{"id": "88a5edbb-b52f-425b-8552-4b5c311198b1", "value": "A large concave moulding."}
{"id": "4d4d19f4-a98a-46a6-8f6d-a9be06d4fe01", "value": "A moulding which projects beyond the face of a panel or frame, usually found in panelling or in doors."}
{"id": "4c6b2519-a1bd-4c42-81a5-cd4376c7cf76", "value": "An ornamental moulding whose curved, segmented form resembles that of a scallop shell."}
{"id": "f3c9f29a-02bd-429b-966e-5559e62e393d", "value": "A small semicircular moulding."}
{"id": "f11efc0c-7dda-401b-8e86-642a38fbc937", "value": "A concave moulding where the profile is a quarter of a circle."}
{"id": "4c81bdc5-292e-4c28-b010-4796afe7599f", "value": "A small moulding on the top of the architrave in the Doric order."}
{"id": "ed63db8e-caf6-4d91-9334-1bd53019f71d", "value": "A continuous series of ornaments within a horizontal moulding."}
{"id": "a368b0f9-18d2-4e8c-9f94-2200ac460a98", "value": "A decorative S-shaped moulding, usually placed at the top of a cornice, with a concave lower half and a convex upper half."}
{"id": "d061fc7b-500a-49d6-a385-46332248da4c", "value": "A small convex moulding, often decorated with beads and reels."}
{"id": "3af9c95e-3ea9-4b73-9b30-f204b521cdd9", "value": "A moulding which is small, convex and circular."}
{"id": "cb7e4997-a535-4461-bb41-4e4c48bb1ec8", "value": "A decorative moulding featuring a geometric pattern suggesting the crenelles and merlons of a battlement."}
{"id": "4885d38c-6f7a-4dc8-8c3e-992e373e877f", "value": "A decorative moulding featuring a repeating star-like motif carved in relief."}
{"id": "2bb60647-e75a-4a9c-92ca-7cae7245dc4f", "value": "A series of concentric mouldings decorating the curved face of an arch."}
{"id": "2c4c306c-8719-48fa-bdc2-d8f3654b298f", "value": "A horizontal, moulded band, usually projecting, running across a wall, often indicating the position of a building's interior floor."}
{"id": "5d370851-bb8f-40fa-acb7-ade8b0fc7174", "value": "A moulding that projects from a wall above an exterior opening and is shaped to channel rainwater away from it."}
{"id": "a188f5a0-279f-43f2-8c48-47b77bc01758", "value": "A plain moulding of semi-circular section."}
{"id": "42e2f12f-6279-419c-8f20-9ee823ba7f40", "value": "A rounded or convex moulding, such as an ovolo or torus."}

{"id": "4b1fe8d4-cca6-4361-8753-21c6630a082b", "value": "A termination, either in the form of a decorative feature or a right-angle applied to the end of the moulding, of a label, dripstone or string course."}

{"id": "6bbc70d2-2d23-45d9-ab4e-c9df022a769d", "value": "A plain, narrow moulding or area, sometimes projecting, separating two decorated mouldings or features such as the vertical grooves on a fluted column."}
{"id": "93ce5b67-b50a-4422-b9cd-4b3edadcb5c1", "value": "A moulding on an entablature that is between the frieze and the corona."}
{"id": "5a939222-da09-48a0-947d-5b500a69c6ab", "value": "An ornamental moulding consisting of a series of small, regularly placed squared or rounded blocks."}
{"id": "51bab568-cb74-4d48-aa47-dc9c5a578168", "value": "A Classical convex moulding, often decorated with egg-and-dart or similar motifs."}
{"id": "23e395ad-f650-49e8-a7a6-de84d314950c", "value": "An ovolo moulding below the abacus of a Doric or Ionic Capital."}
{"id": "42aeeb49-e090-4059-bd4a-4067c034e679", "value": "A decorative moulding cosisting of two ogee-forms with joined faces."}
{"id": "294fa1a4-28e9-40ad-9544-43c22fa6d53e", "value": "A decorative moulding shaped to resemble a length of cable or twisted rope."}

{"id": "5f3fd193-1c4c-4bcb-830a-e42eb7514706", "value": "An ornamental contour given to the angles or features of a building, whether a projection or a cavity, such as a cornice, an architrave or an astragal."}
{"id": "dfe8f11f-5c50-49e6-a80b-62cc07549392", "value": "A hollow moulding, often enriched, similar to a scotia or cavetto, used in Gothic jambs and cornices."}
{"id": "8c48d6f6-646a-4d35-8823-d851ea28e14c", "value": "A decorative feature in the form of small pyramids in a continuous line."}
{"id": "a259504e-48c2-4bfe-a2a3-6311e7f985c7", "value": "An exterior, vertical pipe that carries rainwater from a roof's guttering, usually to a drain."}
{"id": "beec4227-2907-4eab-bf15-9b86e918b38e", "value": "A pipe or channel to carry water outwards from a gutter or behind a parapet. If decorated with grotesque heads it is called a gargoyle."}
{"id": "b64c34e9-40f2-418f-b80a-fe373e694218", "value": "A gutter running behind a parapet wall, the water channelled by it being discharged from holes in the wall."}
{"id": "29dabe6b-eb6b-4b32-8863-821f167d4474", "value": "A trough or watercourse constructed to collect rainwater from a roof and channel it towards a drain or pipe."}
{"id": "b5d958f0-465c-4a85-8554-8a60d78cea27", "value": "A V-shaped gutter."}
{"id": "c85406ef-8c39-4b28-8d50-5da629962e6b", "value": "A plan featuring a doorless entry to a lobby in front of an axial chimney-stack."}
{"id": "067d18cd-a27e-40ed-88b1-3954f52dd253", "value": "A plan in which the front entrance opens into a lobby opposite to an axial chimney stack."}

{"id": "81960e22-ec1f-4998-a291-04c07e51fcf8", "value": "A large tank or cask for storing or holding goods, whether liquid, such as chemicals or fermenting beer, or dry, often during a production process."}

{"id": "ae980138-1f3f-4477-ab2b-201fbaf801f7", "value": "Specialised fermenting vessel consisting of a two-storey system consisting of a shallow chamber approximately 2m high above which is a walled deck."}
{"id": "9734eafa-af59-402b-92dd-09950f96067e", "value": "A two dimensional image using paint applied to the surface of a ceiling."}
{"id": "fbac1c86-8f62-420b-b63c-a7b0d7e0a8db", "value": "A two dimensional image using paint applied to plasterwork whilst the plaster is still damp."}
{"id": "57cf5113-7159-4f1b-8553-757f3baa65f5", "value": "A two dimensional image using paint applied to the surface of a wall."}

{"id": "b6842857-0cfd-46bc-b4a8-bff864126374", "value": "A water-drain connected to a stone bowl within a niche in the south wall of a chapel, used to receive the water in which the priest washed his hands and rinsed the Chalice."}
{"id": "8b42f492-60ac-4a56-96df-3bf61a7a7de0", "value": "One of a series of chapels which project symmetrically from an apse or ambulatory at the east end of a church."}
{"id": "c26f6a70-39af-4868-a8f7-1e2266109e96", "value": "The area that contains the ambulatory, apse and chapels. Usually found in larger churches, monasteries and cathedrals."}

{"id": "9885f585-5429-4934-ae3b-1cd85703ffca", "value": "A building, room or area, often within or attached to a church or other building, serving as a place of worship. Where a monument, use the Thesaurus of Monument Types."}

{"id": "5c409bd3-2f78-4661-986a-14b8a79ef958", "value": "A lobby or chapel at the western entrance of a church. Sometimes a place of burial, an area reserved for women, or a place where monks could meet female relatives."}

{"id": "99b131a3-a4f7-43dd-8f75-6fa5ba21e802", "value": "A chapel, often attached to or screened off inside a church, endowed for the celebration of masses principally for the repose of the founder?s soul."}
{"id": "b8045f88-67be-4fcd-ac3f-e58a4f616617", "value": "A chapel that radiates from an apsidal end of a cathedral or church."}
{"id": "a194b501-eb1d-4969-bac7-5fbb4dea19ae", "value": "A chapel dedicated to the Virgin, usually east of the chancel."}
{"id": "febad093-a0ff-4486-a07e-07399194ec4a", "value": "A thin timber, usually sloping on both sides, fixed to the floor between the jambs of a doorway."}
{"id": "b4e456ec-b51f-491c-a475-822b72577942", "value": "A wooden, metal or stone strip attached to the floor between the door posts in a doorway covering the joint between two floor surfaces."}
{"id": "1e5c27c4-e089-4c32-87c8-41d39c4b8975", "value": "A grave or sepulchre enlosed or covered by a memorial."}

{"id": "f542bf96-d406-4201-be49-c42f219a7542", "value": "A recess, usually situated in the north wall of a chancel, often canopied, containing a decorated tomb chest representing the burial and resurrection of Christ."}
{"id": "b1c640e9-ba4c-4428-854a-aef558c52a19", "value": "A pediment with a gap at its apex, sometimes filled with an urn or other decorative feature."}
{"id": "51410bed-b98f-47d1-8033-3bee14f0c1b3", "value": "A pediment with a gap at the centre of its base."}
{"id": "be6e9451-22c3-45b0-b686-85d059f1cda5", "value": "A roof with a bow-shaped, segmental timber truss which has the space between its members filled by a lattice of crossing diagonal rods."}
{"id": "d4656eab-0b20-41dd-95d7-54f4cbd4dce7", "value": "A bowstring truss with the space between its members filled by a lattice of crossing diagonal rods."}
{"id": "1241f0bd-456a-4f87-97eb-3da278e59196", "value": "A vault with a ceiling or undersurface subdivided by ribs into bays or webs."}

{"id": "1911ff85-8392-4a07-827a-cbcc444ceb16", "value": "An arched half-rib applied to the lateral wall surface in a vaulted bay, its function, rather than structural, being to complete the pattern of the vault's main ribs."}
{"id": "82e9cfba-e565-4b6f-b0a3-6c3577dceedf", "value": "A room or space with an arched ceiling or roof, the depth of which exceeds its span."}
{"id": "86ce5a57-8996-43aa-bdd2-1b48c0ceb990", "value": "A tertiary vault rib, usually employed for decorative purposes, that links one intersection of the main ribs to another."}
{"id": "b17b8163-3216-4d13-9d58-db4ae6319ecb", "value": "A semi-circular or pointed vault uninterrupted by cross vaults, the ceiling bearing a resemblence to a tunnel or the inside of a barrel."}
{"id": "cf438c26-5eb4-4e72-8012-caa84b790376", "value": "A vault created by the intersection of two other vaults set at right angles to each other and of equal size."}

{"id": "e265105f-6c77-45ec-935d-c2e75c39c634", "value": "A term used to describe a vaulted roof where the vault goes from either the newel of a staircase to a wall or from one wall to another where the walls are circular in plan."}
{"id": "9f175be8-dc9c-4f1f-8315-921b7baa0330", "value": "A room set aside for the purpose of reading, such as in a library or a club."}

{"id": "8d0c9c37-7fa4-4d25-934f-445843ade1a5", "value": "A pointed arch in which the arcs comprising it are centred on points both outside and inside the arch so that the point takes the form of a double S, or ogee."}
{"id": "7c9f09ef-f9df-46b0-98cd-58f3cee64d8d", "value": "A porch which is sufficiently large enough to allow a vehicle beneath it."}
{"id": "e3b66267-1cf6-4b7b-9bf8-5ebfa0f014b2", "value": "An entrance large enough for carriages and vehicles leading through a building or wall into an inner courtyard."}
{"id": "435c8831-de97-4c95-a331-084cc4bcc937", "value": "An aisle within a chancel providing access to, and around, the High Altar and surrounding cells."}
{"id": "fcba5cc1-b793-4640-9bda-92ef35ca1255", "value": "A partition or wall behind an altar, often separating the choir and altar from the ambulatory and east chapel."}

{"id": "32180887-60a0-410f-aa69-9370779747d0", "value": "A truss with two curved kerb-principals, which are the short principal rafters rising froma tiebeam to a collar, placed either side of a crown strut."}
{"id": "81cb5a0c-0030-4f87-b6d1-0937245ea4ee", "value": "A short principal rafter that that rises from a tiebeam to a collar."}
{"id": "b937e52a-a8c9-477f-9298-7b0991639308", "value": "A form of entrance closed by a gate."}

{"id": "152d078e-67bb-4438-9ca0-d13548889c8f", "value": "A large, movable barrier, usually an iron or wooden grating with pointed bars along its bottom edge, with its sides set in vertical grooves above a castle's gateway enabling it to be dropped to bar entry."}
{"id": "3f7d3372-3cab-4e58-9284-6d5b89e9d5af", "value": "A movable barrier, usually external, within an opening in a wall, fence, hedge or similar."}
{"id": "fc2dce35-c780-4cff-86fe-c90b324e9a74", "value": "A barrier, usually in the form of a small wall, set to prevent people falling over the side of a bridge, balcony, roof etc."}
{"id": "2ec95242-f2a5-42d2-b49f-e16ee1eb7d68", "value": "A firing step from which standing defenders could fire over the crest of a high parapet."}
{"id": "028993e6-674f-4444-8ac2-7b4efd653799", "value": "An indented parapet consisting of raised parts, called merlons, separated by gaps, or crenelles."}
{"id": "1378093b-154c-49ee-9093-d1b6aca71ae0", "value": "A diagonal brace running from an end of a cross tree to the vertical post to support this."}
{"id": "08dc6e04-2059-4a17-b42f-0548773b6805", "value": "Two intersecting beams set on the ground to support a post, usually for a post mill."}
{"id": "a21c610e-8f0e-4021-bb5d-9a67ef2f379c", "value": "A rail or balustrade that separates the altar from the rest of the church."}
{"id": "1f194033-6f16-4f7f-9313-ed320732f34c", "value": "An elevated table or podium on which to place, or sacrifice, offerings to a god or gods."}
{"id": "0bc6894e-b650-4168-9f05-3b708c888467", "value": "The area or platform at the top of a staircase."}
{"id": "ed612a69-4ac0-4cdf-9f27-d330add0fd86", "value": "An iron bar or rod running through the core of a windmill's windshaft that causes the opening and shutting of the vanes on patent sails."}
{"id": "11eccde3-da6a-430e-b5ac-ac4fa25f4e5f", "value": "A mechanism within a windmill, attached to the striking rod, allowing the opening and closing of the shutters or vanes of patent sails."}
{"id": "dccfb6f7-64e0-4911-8dc9-60dfa9b2982f", "value": "A rectangular dripstone."}
{"id": "2ef7b18d-00aa-4206-b48c-47348f5fe52e", "value": "A roof constructed of horizontal tiebeams and curved trusses."}
{"id": "6db6a578-8b2b-43f7-aa76-222ce69b80f5", "value": "An arched, or bow-shaped, segmental timber truss with its ends tied together by a straight or cambered member."}

{"id": "a3530d24-180c-4afc-9286-934e40a0727d", "value": "Niche intended for pigeons or other birds to nest in, allowing the squabs and eggs to be harvested. Found inside specially built dovecotes and in the walls of other buildings."}

{"id": "9158a8ef-f90d-41ce-bf44-8a77061bf874", "value": "A shelter for doves or pigeons, often containing nesting boxes, either free-standing or built into other structures (barns, towers etc.). If a dedicated, free-standing structure, index with MONUMENT TYPE: DOVECOTE."}

{"id": "14f2e136-ef1c-4514-a393-ae311ce1e4f3", "value": "The wood, stone or brick framework, lining a doorway, from which the door is hung."}
{"id": "07f72dbe-86c6-4551-b035-168c9030230d", "value": "The space in which a door is placed, allowing passage through."}
{"id": "eea4ac7b-d70b-4a9a-a006-2f03eca77ec6", "value": "A triangular gable usually above an entablature."}

{"id": "c7a72f4c-2dbb-40eb-b42e-3f9449e97528", "value": "The face within a pediment, as enclosed by the cornices, or the solid infill of an arch above an impost, sometimes embellished with sculptural or relief ornament."}

{"id": "a8d1606f-f61c-4608-b9d6-6b36452c1cf4", "value": "A bladed wheel attached to the rear, and at right angles to the main sails, of a windmill. Connected to winding gear, the fantail would catch the wind when it changed direction, allowing the mill to move automatically into the wind."}
{"id": "6d955fcc-5b62-4b43-b098-52e3de23fd21", "value": "A pier used to raise a structure or building above ground floor level so that there is open space beneath the structure"}
{"id": "93b1154e-f50c-4eac-9a15-1f1aa2287fe5", "value": "A solid support of masonry to sustain vertical pressure and frequently each of the pillars from which an arch springs."}
{"id": "72b84661-1da2-4c1d-adee-b7399bac2209", "value": "An area within a large fireplace where it is possible to sit."}
{"id": "895ed526-8c26-4d9c-b0b7-765869a988a0", "value": "The heat-resistant wall, or sometimes decorative cast iron panel, at the back of a fireplace."}
{"id": "8405096c-2504-4a53-82a9-61ae168cbbb2", "value": "The opening at the base of a chimney stack."}

{"id": "51aa67e9-16bd-427f-b009-40217701ce5a", "value": "A room where fittings such as saddles and harnesses for horses are usually kept."}

{"id": "c88ce8d5-6d17-4990-9ac2-ddd5a7c8a886", "value": "A buttress set away from the structure it supports, joined to it by an arch."}
{"id": "54565325-faf8-4334-a351-8646a824c5b7", "value": "A plan in which the chimney stack backs onto the cross passage between a building's two entrances."}
{"id": "1d45105b-e5f3-4f8a-9a3e-0c43d037340d", "value": "A hearth, normally placed clear of the walls, without a chimney stack or hood above."}
{"id": "44cfcec9-9c11-4e50-9d42-a961d2c6339b", "value": "The area directly in front of a fireplace or the floor of a firecplace itself."}

{"id": "1494a843-eebc-4c74-9987-d3d4c24f71b7", "value": "An engaged column, that is one attached to a wall."}

{"id": "cfad63e2-8fa8-483f-ad51-f7c463588008", "value": "A regular structural subdivision or compartment within a building, defined by dividing walls or the positions of the principal supporting members."}
{"id": "328bd389-ee1f-493c-b3df-5865f624f6bd", "value": "A short bay, usually in a hall, commonly as a smoke bay or for a cross-entry."}
{"id": "866077fd-ec5e-484b-8af1-20ea0a4c35fa", "value": "A bay in a two storeyed house open to the roof to allow smoke to escape."}
{"id": "589b5d55-5f29-43ef-aa58-92d6354b2af9", "value": "A channel, usually placed upstream of a mill, that carries water from a river or other water source to a waterwheel."}
{"id": "c3a14aaf-792e-46c3-8f6b-aad33cdf36d1", "value": "A channel that returns water that has been used to turn a waterwheel back to the river or source from which it came."}
{"id": "34706cf1-956f-47a1-8666-cb4749ef951a", "value": "A plinth or pedestal, sometimes decorated, and sometimes supporting statuary, placed at the apex and lower extremity of a pediment."}
{"id": "54a77d05-a1ee-4e16-aa83-f1ad8a8bbfdf", "value": "A covered ambulatory, usually arcaded, arranged around three or four sides of a quadrangle in a monastic or collegiate establishment."}
{"id": "8c003f55-0b4f-46a7-b603-767477e9ef10", "value": "A porch in front of the solid wall of a cloister."}
{"id": "6a7c5940-f125-49a4-bc7e-623e889aea7a", "value": "A wooden bar sliding from a long channel at one side of a doorway into a socket in the other jamb so as to bar the door."}
{"id": "682ccf1e-546f-47c2-ba80-b39d98be2200", "value": "A small apse."}

{"id": "5f246c00-69cc-47b5-9634-09dca0830c31", "value": "A polygonal or semicircular recess projecting from an external wall, often with a rounded vault."}
{"id": "4a71248d-4e9c-4383-a3ad-c22249a7a13b", "value": "A vertical upright on either side of a door."}
{"id": "e6147ee5-43a2-4c95-af82-3cd8a4875531", "value": "The vertical lining of a doorway, window or other opening."}
{"id": "3e726666-8e4f-45f5-9270-a7ddf61063b1", "value": "Part of a large church, east of the nave, appropriated for singers and clergy."}
{"id": "10a17599-3202-48bd-9295-d85a1d391461", "value": "A room in which food is prepared."}
{"id": "ee501c57-dd9a-4227-8d70-4192b4751f0a", "value": "A brace which is cut to a double curve."}
{"id": "8bf57f9c-cccf-4bf9-ac3d-a8ed1391141c", "value": "A strategically placed aperture in the wall of a fortification through which guns and cannon can fire upon an invading force."}
{"id": "748e27f6-b859-4bdc-b53c-03b91f17abf8", "value": "An iron plate connecting two or more timbers together."}

{"id": "1eec8554-8a7c-4ac7-a9ec-385172ad78fb", "value": "A mechanism, either automated or consisting of winches and pulleys, that raises sacks of grain on ropes or chains from one floor of a mill to another, usually through one or a series of trap doors."}
{"id": "488fc2ae-4e6f-4789-b336-95d8ec3e3fa2", "value": "The main vertical beam standing at the centre of a post mill carrying the bearing upon which the body of the mill rotates."}
{"id": "95be00e4-2c3e-4b68-aa1c-47bf223fce49", "value": "A duct or channel for hot air to travel through."}
{"id": "00a174d1-dfa8-4944-bb17-455a696e29e1", "value": "A substantial vertical member, usually a component of a main framework."}
{"id": "9e7e114e-e113-4c5c-b89b-04ac0571d685", "value": "A channel or pipeline that feeds water to a waterwheel."}
{"id": "0cde5e6e-cddc-4734-9d27-1702d2dbdd52", "value": "A gate or valve that controls the flow of water from a reservoir, harbour, etc.."}
{"id": "85faa2e5-657d-436a-9626-b6c7cc6ff6d4", "value": "A horizontal timber positioned at the bottom of a framed wall into which posts and studs are tenoned."}
{"id": "8243d88e-a8e9-4142-a745-8d0f3e8bbfcd", "value": "A frame to a structure formed by precast concrete beams placed in pairs."}
{"id": "203f5cef-9c86-4f47-a43f-a3f57a9a3fe9", "value": "A structural member that supports a purlin. Use PRINCIPAL RAFTER where the principal is also a common rafter."}
