{"id": "9c08b2d1-1f06-4349-b64a-fd4e45bebe07", "value": "An opening in the ridge of a roof intended to provide ventilation or an outlet for smoke; also the hood on such an opening that prevents rain entering."}

{"id": "99305a00-f371-4810-8240-24c2f4e86ffa", "value": "A defined portion of a surface, often a wall lining or door, usually rectangular, which may be recessed, level with or proud of its surrounding surface and may be framed by mouldings or channels."}
{"id": "8f71b7fa-c0db-4bec-86e5-ede2b46f361a", "value": "The area at the end of an axle or shaft around which a wheel, bearing etc. pivots or rotates."}
{"id": "19a5f64d-a33d-4f32-8242-95fe5da5027b", "value": "The large wooden framework that supports the grinding wheels in a corn mill."}
{"id": "e79d0f55-f7d6-41b1-b172-025f2402d95a", "value": "Short vertical timbers which go from the rafters to the inner plate on a thick wall."}

{"id": "74dadf66-6b0e-4b7e-b691-0a18c308da95", "value": "A large approximately triangular stone at the foot of a gable, cut to have a horizontal bed and a top conforming, wholly or in part, to the slope of the gable."}
{"id": "da8ec096-853b-4608-8334-e73881b6e283", "value": "A mass of stone or brick built against or as part of a wall to provide additional strength to it."}
{"id": "63c6bdb2-6763-4e32-b459-7bd58c8269a8", "value": "A flat, horizontal piece of timber or masonry projecting from or recessed into a wall to hold objects."}
{"id": "014d68ab-e4bc-4127-98b2-330276f23e8d", "value": "The lower, horizontal surface of a room on which people walk. Can also mean a storey of a building."}
{"id": "e46b4d9e-d1ef-43a8-94af-c7cafc12a60a", "value": "A recess within a wall or room."}

{"id": "869d153e-b5e5-4c4b-b0da-7c79eb8e311e", "value": "A framework of crossed or parallel wooden or metal bars placed over an opening to prevent access but allow the passage of air, light, water etc."}
{"id": "e5ee2563-fd08-4ebe-9090-740cb9994b49", "value": "The top part of a column, often decorated."}
{"id": "efaac96a-c73c-477a-8f68-e9de4f9f52ab", "value": "A gulley in the form of a circle for holding vertical posts in the walls of iron age round houses."}
{"id": "8a08f823-2f18-4521-a2d8-3e07d91a7894", "value": "An inclined member used to support laths under a roof covering. Normally one of a pair."}
{"id": "5834b5f0-c551-4360-a3b4-5ed848b1c765", "value": "A stone or brick used on a corner to reinforce it and also as decoration."}
{"id": "98f21581-3513-42db-bb46-f7214d9c3964", "value": "The exterior upper covering, and its supporting structure, of a building."}
{"id": "ece753b4-e17e-4aed-893c-d165febc6267", "value": "An open grating of wrought iron, bronze, wood etc., forming a screen to a door, window or other opening, or used as a divider."}
{"id": "7ae1a2d5-32ab-47f5-8699-ec8fe3f3ec77", "value": "A chamber usually used for sleeping."}
{"id": "d629a049-9420-46f8-8019-2c6d1136f7d8", "value": "A flat, horizontal strip, block or moulding, sometimes decorated, on a facade or interrupting an architectural feature such as a column."}
{"id": "e5e73be6-9a2b-4bd3-b70a-3766002b760e", "value": "A type of foundation in the form of a post sunk into the ground to support a building platform."}
{"id": "73b298a7-f81f-4109-910c-b8fe9ea68ee2", "value": "A float or pontoon supporting a flexible steel roadway as part of a Mulberry Harbour."}
{"id": "4a50a737-ca0d-4812-92da-71d6924ca5bd", "value": "An aperture cut obliquely in a wall, usually of a chancel, affording a view between the high altar and the aisles or side chapels."}

{"id": "4c8eacc9-7195-42ac-8632-d8b84fd25e5e", "value": "A device, monogram or symbol incised in stonework by a mason as a means of identifying his work. Particularly common in Romanesque and Gothic buildings."}
{"id": "0897d394-ee1e-4961-b327-6abffa0b31fe", "value": "A horizontal member of a wall frame between posts or studs, also the horizontal member in panelling, a panelled door or a window."}
{"id": "2cf9b610-33f0-4878-92db-09531e690a39", "value": "A raised platform at the end of a hall on which the high table sat, though sometimes used to describe the table itself."}
{"id": "8d74b7e5-4c70-40c2-bdf6-1601f93ebf42", "value": "Horizontal timbers laid parallel to each other on which flooring is laid and to which a ceiling is fixed."}
{"id": "83d4fec9-668c-4dd3-80dc-6277ba42450a", "value": "A stone ring built to enclose and sometimes revet a burial mound or cairn."}
{"id": "ec4fcd74-5e0f-439f-92b8-44af1ad73005", "value": "A housing, normally of triangular section, in a post to take the end of a prop, to hold the post upright during construction."}
{"id": "a771be4a-6068-4d6a-b1db-1f4506d4e7e4", "value": "The under surface of an arch, lintel or projecting architectural feature."}
{"id": "4ac620f3-fdc2-4c2c-a8c9-746eadc338a5", "value": "A concave groove or series of grooves."}
{"id": "640c17ec-cbb5-456a-9d91-669c9d5480c7", "value": "A short timber supporting end of joists or rafters to facilitate an opening, such as a door or dormer."}
{"id": "cca7e2c9-dfa0-423e-b9d8-66ec2b0a2238", "value": "A framed fireplace hood built on a bressumer and extending from one outer wall to the other or to a spere."}
{"id": "99292132-47ce-4352-b521-a2039c0ecba8", "value": "A pedestrian passageway, often elevated, connecting two buildings or sections within a building."}
{"id": "97dad166-64b7-477c-84d6-6950fbd39063", "value": "Solid masonry placed to counteract the lateral thrust of a vault or arch."}
{"id": "875ca54c-8c0f-45fb-bb4e-61fc8eda61ac", "value": "A wedge shaped stone or brick forming part of an arch or vault, with its radiating sides coinciding with the radii of that arch."}
{"id": "69175d77-e482-4512-9cd2-faefce206fda", "value": "A combination of timbers to form a frame placed at intervals and carrying the purlins."}
{"id": "2401266b-3a7a-4274-a005-090ac986f0cf", "value": "A housing for one or more bells, usually gabled or roofed."}

{"id": "85823f95-061e-471f-b06e-e257ce70064e", "value": "The side compartment of a building, usually a church, hall or barn, separated from the main body of the building by an arcade; or a passage allowing access to rows of seats in an auditorium or church."}
{"id": "56f0ffdd-5df9-427e-a2c5-09404a2ed2eb", "value": "A timber set on the back of a cruck blade to carry a purlin."}
{"id": "93a936f9-ed51-493a-8a9e-dbc06929022b", "value": "A structure, part of a structure or area constructed from plain bricks."}
{"id": "c1516fda-356c-4c3a-8e52-5e8443390893", "value": "A timber frame placed in the bell chamber of a church tower or belfry designed to hold the bells."}
{"id": "cb72d63e-43ca-4cfd-8278-9d5199bf87e6", "value": "A vertical, circular member, usually load-carrying. Where separate, use monument type."}
{"id": "c3efc8ba-a5d7-4893-a317-c456a5d4c4d9", "value": "A horizontal member spanning an opening and providing support to the wall above the opening."}
{"id": "53f25be0-5a60-428c-adad-86e12f2d096b", "value": "A projection left on a stone block to allow it to be hoisted into position."}
{"id": "4ca8824d-8435-4289-9760-ccadff1ffa7c", "value": "A vertical member standing without support."}

{"id": "5f951813-8233-4abd-830c-9b2bf8030709", "value": "A large gearwheel which, together with a smaller gear called a pinion, connects two parrallel shafts and, in a corn mill, drives the stone nuts."}
{"id": "fec8b837-3fc9-4c1b-b1fe-cf90466ffcdf", "value": "The large main axle on which a waterwheel, which turns the shaft, and a pitwheel are mounted."}
{"id": "d95892c9-4e73-4c05-a9fb-dca2f7cdb976", "value": "A row of columns that carry arches or an entablature."}

{"id": "b8f3501e-9847-4187-a735-b3f015231406", "value": "A large vertical stone forming part of a structure. If the structure is roofed, the orthostat will stretch from the floor to the roof as a single slab."}

{"id": "9e85a296-e290-4cdf-8b21-0498ccabf107", "value": "Any structural component, usually of wood, which is believed to have derived from a vessel. Double index with the appropriate type of structural component eg. BEAM or if known the original term from the MARITIME FIXTURES AND FITTINGS thesaurus."}

{"id": "315c58a3-086e-4201-aa2a-5d603f131cd7", "value": "The quasi-triangular area between, and defined by, the upper sections of a pair of adjacent arches, or between the curve of an arch and the angle of a surrounding frame or structure."}
{"id": "0dae8c11-78a8-4dc5-aaa5-a02a1a8b5f91", "value": "A vertical piece of wood fixed on corners of walls to help the fixing of plaster and to protect against damage to the plaster."}
{"id": "d85c633c-158d-4a2e-951e-d43d543861bf", "value": "The wedge shaped end of a bridge pier designed to break the current of water."}
{"id": "a67cab29-6820-4980-9fcd-5d25b09f40a0", "value": "An inclined course on top of a projecting sill, cornice etc., designed to throw off rainwater."}

{"id": "3e5f2ed7-1d6c-42ff-8630-04b627e9828c", "value": "A small timber fixed to a wall to support items such as cladding. Also a strip of timber fixed across two or more parallel boards to join them together or conceal their join."}

{"id": "fb9b39db-5da3-4ac6-978c-e4f305b5fdca", "value": "The first driven gearwheel on the vertical shaft within a corn mill which meshes with the brake wheel in a windmill, or the pit wheel in a watermill."}
{"id": "f52f9259-6e0e-4919-8c51-165a27498e45", "value": "A short timber set on top of two cruck blades."}
{"id": "2faa619b-535a-467c-b169-ce61287e5b09", "value": "A straight brace from rafter to collar in a common rafter truss."}
{"id": "9e2fe2ca-6031-47f6-a2c5-cdc161081e6b", "value": "One of the rolls forming the sides of an ionic capital, joining the volutes of the front and rear faces."}

{"id": "bdadd933-b3a8-4353-80db-2c15179c531d", "value": "The structure consisting of a series of balusters supporting a rail or coping, and sometimes a base and pedestal, on a parapet, balcony or staircase."}

{"id": "07393996-64ce-4bad-8e7a-5e4760880227", "value": "A four-armed metal coupling, positioned at the centre of a windmill's sails, connected to the front of the striking rod and the shutter bars of all the sails, causing the shutters to open and close."}
{"id": "d861f657-48a9-4779-a0f3-ed54e6749d41", "value": "A projecting, sometimes decorated, finish to a moulding, chamfer, label, hood-mould or string-course."}

{"id": "6a60f1b2-f633-4995-8a44-815bae44e782", "value": "An adjustable, horizontal beam, supporting the vertical stone spindle in a water or windmill, which allows the gap between the grinding stones to be varied."}
{"id": "6c6af687-e22f-4714-813c-e05448a5377b", "value": "The lowest part of a structure, such as a pier, or the section of an order on which the shaft of a column sits."}
{"id": "7a83e3b9-5b44-4c0c-80fe-d3a5534d9221", "value": "A plain area situated between the top of the shaft and the capital of a Renaissance Tuscan or Doric Order column."}
{"id": "80f5c3af-39b6-41fd-ad63-179ef001b15b", "value": "A structure, part of a structure or area consisting of plain masonry."}
{"id": "b8178d98-e726-44c7-a1a7-52373429fde7", "value": "The main axle projecting through the front of a windmill on which the sails are mounted."}
{"id": "039c2b7e-a7cd-457b-b900-bf89f9569c17", "value": "A wall, usually perforated to allow free passage of air, supporting the ground-floor joists of a building."}
{"id": "3ac66ca8-e305-43bf-abe1-f1902988973c", "value": "A recess, often containing shelves and usually fitted with a door or doors, used for the storage of items."}
{"id": "708e4333-49ad-42ce-8168-2f8f220f298c", "value": "A stone edging on a footway dividing it from a carriageway."}
{"id": "95cae867-441e-4f35-94d4-1e5d78cb0019", "value": "A horizontal timber set in the plane of a roof's slope and supporting common rafters."}
{"id": "f1f46b83-14cb-4b13-8ba7-946e85972cda", "value": "The lowest part, or base, of a structure, sometimes built into the ground, on which the weight of the whole rests."}
{"id": "54a1c22a-6480-4520-9e48-6645be0e52be", "value": "A vertical timber in a truss, descending from the ridge, and projecting below the lower transverse timber, normally used with scissor beams."}
{"id": "f9d4edf3-a0d9-4500-86b5-ef1861b04c80", "value": "The part of a column between the capital and the base."}
{"id": "7fbb6a1d-669a-475d-822e-1925b470e7a4", "value": "A hollow, cylindrical structure or tube made of clay, lead, steel, wood etc. through which gas, oil, water or other liquids can be conveyed."}

{"id": "87d05fb5-2d0f-44c1-b95a-33d98127f5dc", "value": "A plain stone course, sometimes projecting, above a cornice and counterbalancing the cantilevered sections of stone, or at the base of a building."}

{"id": "3dd9ba43-0362-4097-aea7-b2814023e146", "value": "The upper parts of walls carried on arcades or colonnades in the nave, choir or transepts of a church or hall, rising higher than the lean-to roofs of the aisles and pierced with windows to allow light to penetrate."}
{"id": "5e58f62a-705b-4d4f-979b-29d9a5435cb9", "value": "A vertical partition used to separate one area from another."}
{"id": "6f058451-abe5-4de5-aeb6-4b8515140c08", "value": "A pad on which a post rests to support part of a structure."}
{"id": "d4484a6d-d420-40c1-b3ba-37cfdc844da9", "value": "A funnel-like container from which grain or other material is fed to a grinding mechanism below."}

{"id": "e2266711-2757-402a-bc2d-db4735fa7bf7", "value": "A cutting, bank or block positioned against the wall of a trench, fort, parapet etc. to allow riflemen to shoot over the crest of the wall or parapet from a standing position."}
{"id": "2c5d8104-0d4f-4328-b63e-20f082412bc8", "value": "The principal longitudinal member or spine of a windmill sail, extending from the stock and supporting the sailbars."}
{"id": "4b18af00-e45d-4b9b-a1cc-df934880a573", "value": "A small support designed to help support a weight, such as that of a projecting member."}
{"id": "ffd0e613-50f0-4980-8817-35c96c3849ef", "value": "A non-structural covering, such as tile, slate, wood etc., applied to an exterior wall."}
{"id": "8def3c4a-4222-4f0f-b36d-a1883a0248d2", "value": "A tall, circular, polygonal or square structure rising from a roof, tower, turret etc., tapering to a slender point."}
{"id": "709fbbc8-a993-4efe-bf36-66801ed1cc3a", "value": "A general term given to all horizontal timbers laid on walls or posts in order to support other timbers."}
{"id": "5f22a58d-d4f8-4b27-9665-dd5b6d47be62", "value": "A board fixed at the gable end to purlins, often decorated."}
{"id": "46bc9872-42f8-4b17-8409-7705d0e7cbfe", "value": "A thin wooden slab or tile used in quantity as a roof or wall covering."}
{"id": "4f143a7d-5db9-45eb-9a60-8e1c51145c94", "value": "A covered walkway attached to a building."}
{"id": "78bb429b-9762-4ed4-86fb-ea30511e5c77", "value": "The point or block from which an arch or vault starts. The block generally has a horizontal base and sloped top."}
{"id": "17e6beda-d620-4a70-b6a0-ad39bef4a96f", "value": "A moulding on a flat or vaulted ceiling, suggesting a structure or forming a pattern derived from vaulting.."}
{"id": "b6dd1326-4424-4f81-a37f-48ae8e99cdee", "value": "A subsidiary member, usually vertical, in a framed wall or partition."}

{"id": "730dc817-5385-4beb-8a4b-0f0ed0188b2b", "value": "A projecting structure in the roof of a mill containing a winch, allowing loads to be lifted clear of the building's wall and protecting the winch from the weather."}

{"id": "5d721e3d-f24e-45bb-952b-f76052abdf09", "value": "The horizontal piece of timber or stone forming the bottom of a window, doorway or other opening, usually and properly designed to throw off water."}
{"id": "eddad920-49d9-491b-8f6d-bfb5df8b3934", "value": "A metal or stone plate or tablet, usually inscribed, set into a wall, pedestal, floor etc., often serving as a memorial."}
{"id": "37985c75-f204-4579-bc25-dfe5383e733b", "value": "The corner upright bar of a polygonal sash."}

{"id": "ed1a8717-4f74-4ebf-a787-dc5dc89e79e5", "value": "The impost, or point at which a vault rests upon its support, and from which it seems to spring. Hence the term describes the bottom stone of a vault, which lies on the impost."}
{"id": "1a883715-0c43-493c-9207-2f0a538a84ec", "value": "A horizontal member connecting rafters or cruck blades at a point between their feet and the apex of the roof."}
{"id": "4f160d2f-a16b-4f53-86fc-8f2c74ad0ba3", "value": "An ornamental bracket on either side of a doorway supporting a cornice."}
{"id": "ecf0f5ab-a07c-48da-8716-af8223ba19e6", "value": "A base on which a statue, column etc. stands."}

{"id": "6399c42c-dd7c-4a8d-9821-6983f4fefbf9", "value": "A triangular or wedge-shaped timber cocking-piece attached to the upper face of a rafter near its foot in order to reduce the slope above the eaves. Such eaves are referred to as being sprocketed."}
{"id": "10cfa22b-2d81-4827-ab35-90e5a652ffe3", "value": "A flattened rectangular version of a column of one of the classical orders."}

{"id": "fd35238a-80c0-466f-bbde-48575682ca25", "value": "A small tank or cistern, often lead or cast-iron and sometimes ornamented, that collects rainwater from a gutter or channel prior to it being discharged."}
{"id": "122b8a16-b8cf-4dc8-a450-0c224384df28", "value": "A rectangular recess along the edge of a timber to receive a shutter, door or window."}
{"id": "1d6cb422-fa5a-45b6-958f-157b942b8b59", "value": "A protective earthern mound."}
{"id": "39c87f6e-a3c0-4ff5-82e5-0360e88e05f8", "value": "A short timber linking two pieces of timber."}
{"id": "e2bed031-d8ff-425d-ab23-ca3539f61d1c", "value": "A protective covering applied to the top of a wall, chimney, gable etc., usually curved, sloping or ridged to prevent rainwater settling."}
{"id": "b1bd1e9c-9f7f-4020-952f-0e796076bfcd", "value": "A triangular piece of wood used to raise slates next to a wall or similar."}
{"id": "131aa35e-3f0e-4dc5-a8ce-6ec1c609a826", "value": "A pier made up of several shafts against it. The shafts can be attached or detached."}

{"id": "f6d60b0d-08be-40bf-b8dd-d5d7d8811501", "value": "A large shallow pan, usually metal, in which seawater or brine is evaporated for the extraction of salt. The name is also often applied to the exterior pits or ponds used for the same purpose (see Thesaurus of Monument Types)."}
{"id": "f7de0125-b5fb-4b49-a4a3-0663313aee64", "value": "An inclined wooden trough which channels grain evenly from the feed hopper into the eye of the stones in a corn mill."}
{"id": "3577a824-bbdb-4d41-8b2e-c17db05cdef2", "value": "A small piece of timber occupying the angle between two other timbers."}
{"id": "e2348f15-5b5c-4741-9e82-e8a8ff458685", "value": "A horizontal member supporting the posts in a timber framed structure."}
{"id": "3c836340-b981-407e-a7e9-9c3381c79f87", "value": "An item used to fasten, bind or join one item to another."}
{"id": "c38ecac6-754b-4c48-8bd6-ff159adbae95", "value": "A pole projecting to the rear of a post mill to allow the sails to be moved into the wind."}

{"id": "aba9fb4e-5d4a-419e-96d2-3142a6fdb560", "value": "A series of flat-topped structures, usually wooden or stone, on which a person places their feet when ascending or descending, facilitating movement from one level to another."}
{"id": "e507da3b-2626-4ad1-92b1-aeead0abd630", "value": "The flue or channel that funnels smoke from a fire."}
{"id": "ba9bf2ac-201e-45eb-bb7f-f15f7a1299e2", "value": "Glass that has been coloured by fusing glass with a metallic oxide film or by burning pigment into the surface."}
{"id": "0db9aef4-2ab4-4c50-959a-5555fb85d587", "value": "A usually shallow cut linear feature often used for drainage."}

{"id": "2eea8237-6879-4ced-b0ce-e5e90f47d8d5", "value": "A funnel, connected to an opening in the floor of the tun encasing the grindstones in a corn mill, that carries ground meal away to a bin or sack."}
{"id": "b10b2f1d-53c6-41a6-8c05-52fc987fad68", "value": "A flat, circular stone, usually made of sandstone, used in pairs for grinding corn and other meal."}

{"id": "3763248d-bdd3-4315-baee-10af31115292", "value": "The gearwheel on the upright shaft within a windmill from which secondary drives operating other parts of the machinery are powered. are taken"}
{"id": "4b6dd719-9235-44e2-bc1e-f533aebcfc6e", "value": "The ridge formed at the intersection of two vaulted surfaces."}
{"id": "edc0eacb-a627-421b-9d1f-fd0329529162", "value": "Timber framed construction where a box of horizontal and vertical members is created to support the roof."}
{"id": "1fc26382-a8f1-4ae0-8bbd-c4f1f04b9c23", "value": "Any member that connects two bodies, such as the sloping sides of a roof, to prevent them pulling apart."}
{"id": "6c127d20-4f3b-4f14-be8d-88a126deb1a0", "value": "The hole through which the fuel for a fire is put to start and maintain the fire."}
{"id": "5e8264ee-1f98-4035-b101-100d39321053", "value": "A part of an arch between the apex and the springer."}
{"id": "4924ff42-a687-4047-8b6c-9c8377c55e1c", "value": "A gap which allows air to circulate."}

{"id": "3a58d5e6-2667-46e7-b912-b8a2b57a3b12", "value": "The smallest piece of timber (2-5cms) across used in building, employed on rafters to support the roof covering or in a partition as a base for plaster or external render and wall covering."}
{"id": "cbe57785-9119-4784-9bcb-3a9be7bda95c", "value": "A small hole filled or vacated by a stake, normally driven into the ground."}
{"id": "5caa7adb-f49d-44e6-9511-da57dd54fea5", "value": "A half-pier, corbel or other architectural element, usually situated at the end of an arcade, attached to a wall to support an arch."}
{"id": "fac1b18b-9ae3-449d-adef-0b54e7c692e4", "value": "The rotating top section of a tower or smock mill."}
{"id": "e9b2d360-585f-4ccc-bfdd-262e40228201", "value": "A part of a building or structure that is an element of the construction."}
{"id": "ecfb2edf-ada4-442f-81da-1562127e1feb", "value": "In the Classical Orders, the horizontal assembly of architrave, frieze and cornice carried upon columns and pilasters."}
{"id": "17404f47-b7af-4745-bd25-5116c03ca62d", "value": "A glazed opening in a roof or ceiling."}
{"id": "c6018623-a26e-4d41-ba86-6ab127ee001c", "value": "A large stone laid horizontally to form the roof of a chamber."}

{"id": "c8212a9b-cc10-420c-aaba-61a0e9a4a78c", "value": "A screen, with a wide central opening, or multiple narrower openings, spanning the lower end of a medieval hall, screening the cross entry and defining the screen, or cross, passage."}

{"id": "3d0de0b8-da83-4ea8-8ae2-66a37b02938e", "value": "An opening in a wall that is usually narrow on the outside but widens internally to allow a defender to stand and shoot through the loophole."}
{"id": "7625ad3d-a320-41be-90af-dd3c94803e00", "value": "A wooden nail, round or square in section, used to fix a joint."}
{"id": "693f8b1d-2f9f-4cd9-9c90-77079e1449e7", "value": "A carved, convex block, often richly decorated, at the intersections of vault-ribs, beam-junctions or terminations of mouldings."}
{"id": "15415ccb-a5f7-4508-a712-e81e50123f58", "value": "A member whose purpose is to keep two other members apart, so acting in a state of compression."}
{"id": "99a35d02-3229-4ce4-bf03-302bc1da8db5", "value": "A projecting part of a building that overhangs the wall below it."}
{"id": "e2f4d436-8e43-4baa-8bfd-7727f30a5dd3", "value": "An area or series of tiles applied, usually to an interior floor or wall's surface, for practical or decorative effect."}
{"id": "9b6636b1-d089-4f20-aa24-135301241464", "value": "A short timber laid across the top of a masonry wall to carry a wall plate or the foot of a common rafter."}
{"id": "f38b1284-7c71-4bb1-885e-aeeddd91986c", "value": "A roof, circular in plan, usually semicircular in section, over a circular, square or polygonal base."}
{"id": "1c35eced-0f27-4979-921b-e3c61eaa6fe3", "value": "A canopy suspended, or on pillars, over a throne or altar."}
{"id": "c9b3deb7-db9c-482d-acf6-b59929a949d2", "value": "A raised platform, especially in a theatre or auditorium, for the use of performers or speakers etc."}
{"id": "06f9e4a4-279f-4471-8c59-bc8c13280c78", "value": "A series of arches."}

{"id": "6a59cd5c-c147-4222-a268-de3f48bd7417", "value": "A device, usually wooden, or fabric on a timber frame, designed to catch, and be driven by, the wind in order to power a windmill. For maritime uses see the Thesaurus of Maritime Archaeology."}
{"id": "1c3c1489-b2f7-487f-bc5a-3b11eb6b92e4", "value": "A thin masonry facing or cladding employed to conceal the surface or structure behind it."}
{"id": "33c53272-09ac-475a-9995-961eeacb24d0", "value": "A structure, usually of brick, stone or timber, that encloses or defines a space or room."}
{"id": "b5b712cd-15fd-48c6-9066-fa9424c0b610", "value": "The external face or elevation of a building, especially the principal front."}

{"id": "af8c9fe2-7c3f-40e8-8bb5-025b796782a4", "value": "A short, tapered, vertical stone supporting a rough stone disc so resembling a toadstool, often forming one of several uprights on which a timber structure, such as a granary rests, protecting the building from damp and vermin."}
{"id": "959c6728-112c-4021-bb01-26891f032f69", "value": "A section of stone or brickwork employed in a timber-framed building to fill the spaces between uprights or studs."}

{"id": "610dfd29-baf2-4628-9447-4c8f0a115acf", "value": "A casement, usually wooden, in a mill enclosing the grindstones and preventing the loss of ground material before it is channelled into sacks."}
{"id": "070fa272-bc96-4af2-b048-0c8a36f97f3e", "value": "The main gearwheel in a water mill, sharing the same shaft as the exterior waterwheel but placed within the mill."}
{"id": "7dab4ff3-2106-4577-a7e1-16a73ef95e6a", "value": "A main load-bearing horizontal member."}
{"id": "99db4360-e248-43ff-a554-f8e24f0eaca2", "value": "A diagonal or arched member placed across rafters to stiffen and support a roof structure."}

{"id": "9c201274-ecdf-47ca-970f-c4852ae74abc", "value": "A metallic rod attached to a high point on a building and leading to the earth for the purpose of conducting lightning away from the main body of the building."}
{"id": "3e453c4d-12b2-43ab-84d5-ed462de89a5d", "value": "The surface of a room which conceals overhead structural members."}
{"id": "dd8edbdd-c7d7-4614-8b73-702a53413a3e", "value": "A hinged, sliding or rolling door placed over a window's exterior or interior."}
{"id": "25c11e47-2875-4dfc-985c-c4dc02261ad6", "value": "Pinion which engages with the spur wheel and drives the millstones in a corn mill."}
{"id": "2ae66610-6b74-4cb9-8477-383df4a04180", "value": "The main vertical axle running through the centre of a mill."}
{"id": "27502a0a-ab8a-42e9-bc9c-d1fc2f845608", "value": "A sloping timber in a staircase holding the ends of treads and risers."}
{"id": "deb0f699-9d44-4bc9-b7d7-55be63e10a16", "value": "A framed canopy suspended above the dais or high table at the upper end of a hall."}
{"id": "18f7cfac-94fe-486c-ad95-a19b01e100f4", "value": "A small projection designed to allow space for a bed."}
{"id": "1b376a2c-5bb4-4493-b215-184b1bc71d41", "value": "A stone, usually inscribed, laid during a ceremony to commemorate the founding of a new building"}

{"id": "2423bc6e-ca2e-4188-a6c8-a832eccf606d", "value": "A decorative piece descending vertically from the bottom of a newel on a staircase, or from the junction of barge boards at the apex of a gable."}

{"id": "50e4e991-a089-4c7d-864b-59f8e969afb3", "value": "A panel of often decorated wrought-ironwork forming the arch between two gate-piers or standards or above a gate. Also used for an arched support for a lamp-holder between two standards."}
{"id": "dfd4cc22-5e46-4553-9c35-dbfc41046b6e", "value": "A short timber connecting a cruck blade to a wall above the point at which the blade diverges from it."}
{"id": "856cb94a-627f-4ec1-8723-306763564e59", "value": "A hand operated machine for winding cotton and linen thread into balls - invented in 1802."}
{"id": "9ed140ba-192c-471c-b65c-f27ab3fdc4a5", "value": "The primary mechanism within an engine or device that transmits motion, especially rotary motion, to wheels, cogs, turntables etc."}
{"id": "7f513e8b-9bb2-4259-899c-0e283a40db12", "value": "A grooved block placed in series, alternating with the metopes, in a Doric frieze."}
{"id": "857e44e2-afbf-4b8a-8ab6-eb03280ddcee", "value": "A brace, running from a post to a principal, stiffening an interrupted tiebeam."}
{"id": "356e655e-0f4c-4b0e-b244-350b6ba76d1d", "value": "A brace, parallel to another, in wall framing or arcading, or in trusses between post and tiebeam; also referred to as a duplicate brace."}
{"id": "684cdc59-1e0e-43ac-88f7-58f2bdf778a2", "value": "A brace halved to the inside of studs, and so not visible from outside."}
{"id": "f59c028c-2e84-4a1c-bd7d-79f835489c08", "value": "An inclined timber used to support and provide rigidity to roofs, partitions etc."}

{"id": "79909347-44a0-4394-b5e5-97f1d8321a41", "value": "A long straight timber, halved across other roof timbers, especially running from a wall post or aisle post across the tiebeam to the opposing rafter."}
{"id": "4e512832-4f35-471d-a3a1-c08e86079951", "value": "A short, horizontal brace set between a tiebeam and a wall plate to strengthen the structure."}
{"id": "4f0d63d7-723b-4695-9098-8296a097db92", "value": "A brace running from a vertical to a lower horizontal timber."}
{"id": "78ccbf44-2276-4573-b6b6-5bfd79397787", "value": "A curving, upright timber brace used in roof construction, found in pairs, forming an arch."}
{"id": "3f2d4baf-329f-45f8-8fa8-fb58bdf28fad", "value": "One of a pair of crossing braces halved or lapped across each other, tying a pair of rafters together."}
{"id": "7b31e33f-c3ec-46f2-8a0f-cb295a163215", "value": "A windbrace that bypasses one purlin to be jointed into the next purlin or principal."}
{"id": "b4fd7088-fa11-439e-9e76-511fc44a36ef", "value": "A brace extending from a vertical to a higher horizontal timber."}
{"id": "cd265df6-a516-4389-ba94-f8120e470b4d", "value": "A horizontal brace linking tiebeam and wall plate, or adjacent wall plates at the corner of a hipped roof."}
{"id": "796398c5-f3d7-4297-a495-766276170fac", "value": "A timber running obliquely across a series of common rafters."}
{"id": "527dc6d1-f350-4668-97e2-a4d5f7c6c40b", "value": "A very short brace between post and tiebeam, or post and wall plate."}
{"id": "9406f385-448a-4436-ba43-01947c08fd39", "value": "A hole occupied by a timber post or the void remaining after its removal, usually with packing."}
{"id": "33349ec5-2278-4964-be53-74146a9e00c6", "value": "The space occupied by or left where a post has been."}

{"id": "a7474d92-f3e5-4de8-b2cc-38249030c565", "value": "An enclosed structure of brick, stone or metal in which material is heated or burned, or, in a domestic context, food is cooked, through the continuous radiation of heat from its floor, walls or ceiling."}
{"id": "4098e567-19d9-4457-9a82-c00c897baf3a", "value": "A device for receiving and sending radio-transmitted signals into the atmosphere."}

{"id": "4f92a0be-7fd4-4bd0-9fed-9400f370c715", "value": "A motor in which rotary motion is produced by motive power, usually of water, steam or gas, impinging directly on a series of vanes upon the circumference of a revolving cylinder or disc."}

{"id": "71034ea2-4770-4e5d-8e73-e693b1ed3fec", "value": "A powerful machine comprising a pair of heated cylinders revolving inside a chamber, and used for converting raw rubber into a soft plastic mass by being 'chewed' between knives or teeth projecting from the cylinders."}
{"id": "0cdcbc6e-4a76-4c30-a4ff-02d94a8c263e", "value": "A pulley running on the outside of a belt to improve the effectiveness of a drive."}
{"id": "9b2e52a1-588e-4572-9899-4f6592acc5da", "value": "A machine used to burn and desiccate rubbish."}
{"id": "b820e023-b7c6-4a83-97e6-1c51ba503933", "value": "A machine used for drawing out and twisting together short fibres to make a yarn or thread. Use more specific term where known."}
{"id": "69bdfac9-640a-4a6a-a589-14d96f9cb7e4", "value": "A machine used in the silk industry for applying the final twist to silk threads to make them suitable for weaving into a fabric."}
{"id": "1de9d1d4-1d59-44d1-a04a-10c647136065", "value": "A wheel turned by water to generate mechanical power."}

{"id": "2562bf52-3566-4f66-9459-5cafe1d5c5f6", "value": "A device for raising miners individually from a shaft consisting of two rods, raised and lowered alternately, fitted with small platforms and powered by a waterwheel or steam engine."}
{"id": "df0caf7f-3623-4deb-a307-bf577c946391", "value": "A signal usually mounted on a gantry, be it mechanical or electronic, to provide guidance to traindrivers on access to sections of track."}

{"id": "9fad87d4-375e-4f52-aa50-d83b78574407", "value": "A plant used to sterilize water for use in public bathing establishments, not to be confused with desaliation or purification units for drinking water."}

{"id": "3de7e4e3-f3d5-4292-807a-76cfc1a883ba", "value": "A timber, horse-powered device consisting of a large, rotating drum around which a rope would be wound, hoisting material from a quarry pit, mine shaft etc.."}
{"id": "356b7e92-ed06-4bc5-88ea-d2b49173bd73", "value": "A machine used in the worsted industry for cleaning woollen slivers after gilling and cording."}
{"id": "748145cc-931c-4ac3-937f-bf3819405457", "value": "A cleansing or separating machine used in a corn mill for removing smut from grain before it is ground."}
{"id": "f3316e0e-66dc-48f7-aad6-bb107693b444", "value": "Apparatus using mechanical power for a particular function."}

{"id": "80dd7baa-15af-4d56-a432-74c20fab5de9", "value": "A mechanical component or device that can change the direction of motion of a pump rod from the vertical to the horizontal plane and vice versa."}
{"id": "329daea5-598a-4821-8adb-cfcb626beddd", "value": "A steam-powered machine used for raising materials such as ore or water from a pit or shaft."}
{"id": "b853abe0-a906-4b65-b0ea-fd8644a218b8", "value": "A machine used for weighing objects."}

{"id": "5925e370-b19d-4a39-9d24-e5ef15d2e767", "value": "A hydraulic machine used to magnify the stroke of a hydraulic piston. The pulleys and chains of a crane or other device are attached to the jigger."}
{"id": "e9694e28-74d6-4a8f-a915-90c398ac3bc5", "value": "A device for hoisting, or operating pumps, using water displacement as a lifting and balancing medium."}
{"id": "199ccb55-f095-435a-ab5e-c4ece3260906", "value": "An elevator used to raise locomotives."}

{"id": "88f66f28-322a-4ea5-af38-34a8e7c0cf18", "value": "An ornamental panel or decorative structure situated above a mantelpiece"}
{"id": "5512661c-98e6-43a1-ae08-7da2bc7977fe", "value": "Decorative ornamentation consisting of alternating oval and V-shaped motifs, used to enrich ovolo mouldings."}
{"id": "1d0a2f15-d1ab-4c87-8cec-74112422ca38", "value": "A sculptural or decorative representation of an animal. Includes mythical and fantastical animals such as dragons, centaurs etc."}

{"id": "16a30303-bcba-4c6a-b9aa-0747ac7d8896", "value": "Small 'drops' or conic projections under the mutules (a repeating block motif) and triglyphs (rectangular blocks embellished with vertical grooves) in a Doric entablature."}
{"id": "e3dab6e3-e4b3-41dd-8a59-da4b255c2403", "value": "An area of plasterwork modelled or incised with ornamental designs or motifs."}
{"id": "e37551f7-a089-4850-a588-1253d2cfead5", "value": "A series of panels, usually of wood, combined to line a room."}
{"id": "0ff786c7-b6e0-47ea-9a00-4a6a726ae0f9", "value": "A decorative feature in the style of a flower or plant. Use more specific term."}

{"id": "37842abf-5870-4a05-b14a-0bbdaac77d4b", "value": "A figurative or abstract design in the round or in relief and can be of various materials. For freestanding sculptures see also Monument Types Thesaurus."}

{"id": "ea113971-2034-44a8-a460-ad452e5da3d5", "value": "A display or depiction of authorised armorial bearings, such as the elements of a coat of arms, livery and personal badges and flags, mottoes etc.."}
{"id": "026aae2c-2070-45fb-9e35-9261de114c20", "value": "A component part that is designed deliberately for decorative purposes."}
{"id": "6558a84e-e505-4016-a221-0456fc322300", "value": "Fine art depiction in oil, watercolour or other media on wood panels, canvas or paper"}
{"id": "2f69ad2d-c2f3-4cab-95d1-09ae51c1c659", "value": "Decorative ornamentation in the form of a horn filled with fruit etc."}

{"id": "d95df194-c7c1-4330-9147-e0e4abc08a43", "value": "An arrangement by which panels, screens, vaults or windows are divided into parts of different shapes or sizes by means of moulded stone bars or ribs, called form-pieces or forms in the Medieval period."}

{"id": "34907a01-c354-45e4-85de-60c4088f914e", "value": "A decorative feature, or non-heraldic badge, representing the name of a person connected with a building, often in the form of a graphic pun on the name."}
{"id": "ae259233-222f-42be-8695-832ad0322434", "value": "The shaped projection on the top of a newel post or at the apex of a gable."}
{"id": "88f357cf-8184-4456-a353-7730579093c5", "value": "A decorative, framed tablet, usually bearing an inscription or coat of arms, in the form of a scroll or curving piece of parchment."}
{"id": "4ca959b4-3084-4e90-863e-f387f5503aa9", "value": "An inscription or illustration carved into the surface of a stone wall or other architectural element."}

{"id": "c1395f98-06ac-4bc4-8175-664ee16cf7c1", "value": "Paper, often decorated with a printed pattern, painted or embossed design, and usually provided in rolls and used to line the interior walls of a building for decorative purposes."}

{"id": "8d6fd379-4ccb-4a04-bc5f-1a47e8a3617b", "value": "A decorative, spiral scroll form, thought to have been based upon the shape of a ram's horn, employed in consoles, modillions, the capitals of orders such as the Ionic, Composite and Corinthian etc.."}
{"id": "102208a0-6cbe-4c20-b4b7-634d0d6fdc4b", "value": "An oval or circular decorative feature often bearing an illustration or portrait in light relief."}

{"id": "caee8909-dcfc-4006-aa7b-2cf637d1d47e", "value": "One of a series of small, rectangular blocks arranged like a row of teeth, projecting from the lower part of a cornice in many classical orders."}
{"id": "2c158c7f-0148-467b-91a8-44713c490ebb", "value": "A sculptural or decorative representation of a human figure. Includes mythical and fantastical figures such as Cupid, Atlas etc."}
{"id": "85cc300f-5bf9-4c38-ba69-04c3350825ad", "value": "An inscription on illustration applied to a wall by carving into its plaster to reveal a different colour beneath."}
{"id": "a75a596d-d96c-4488-80c1-78ec6e97b32e", "value": "Decorative ornamentation in the form of interlacing ribbons or cords, usually in an intricate pattern."}

{"id": "7c839d18-374b-4436-a9d7-09120f57cdc8", "value": "A decorative feature of wood, plaster or carved masonry, often used in low relief on ceilings, panels or screens and resembling interlacing leather straps. Popular in the late 16th and early 17th centuries."}
{"id": "748218d7-5704-4e4b-b111-942df3b169d6", "value": "A flat band carrying a motto."}
{"id": "ad5300d3-d993-432b-8ac1-b592daa02990", "value": "A cornice along the sloping edge of a pediment or gable."}
{"id": "d9314e3c-f108-4c8a-a0f9-a8a1744bc775", "value": "A latrine, or privy, situated at the rear of a monastery dormitory."}
{"id": "9860a656-3f7c-4890-9967-32e33cb99cdd", "value": "A truss in which two pairs of arch braces form a continuous curve from the wall-heads or below to meet in the centre of the collar."}
{"id": "b3e0e41e-547a-4b5c-882f-a9633ad73ca9", "value": "A short timber connecting a cruck's timber, or blade, to a wall plate."}
{"id": "9660c893-53c2-4012-8756-436a7478108d", "value": "A mobile crane usually found on a marine or inland quay."}
{"id": "afbe2c55-e44d-4409-b68c-528aa78452c6", "value": "A panel, usually wooden or stone, painted or engraved with an illustration or inscription."}
{"id": "d5c1a25d-7cc4-4cbf-b4e1-fb21522e5e7e", "value": "A roof with four sloping sides, rising from four gables, joining at the apex like a pyramid."}
{"id": "35e1db4e-1751-4600-87a0-6c239b4703dc", "value": "A masonry or brickwork structure projecting above a roof and containing several flues."}
{"id": "6fa1f2cb-ef4d-4035-9f4f-b38fdb1e8281", "value": "Romanesque overlapping arcades, producing a series of pointed arches."}
{"id": "449ac221-5e88-455a-bf86-1797ae849857", "value": "A mobile crane which floats on water."}

{"id": "8e986194-0ed0-4903-a3df-f0b3a58bc865", "value": "A circular stylised ornament, essentially a patera with floral enrichment, associated with classical architecture and occurring on the soffits of coffers, and as the fleuron of the Corinthian abacus."}
{"id": "4c106a65-c556-4434-bd89-21098baab601", "value": "A structure, or building, forming a supplementary and subsidiary part of a main complex."}

{"id": "0e45afd0-e1c5-4df4-9b96-b236ab03c2a0", "value": "An entablature often of great magnificence with bead and reel between fasciae of the architrave, frieze ornamented with continuous sculpture and cornice, with ornate coffers and richly carved modillions."}
{"id": "ef3399b1-d0f7-4f29-b6d2-c4392249648e", "value": "A room for general daily use, usually in a family dwelling."}
{"id": "154fcf6a-fb35-450d-8067-e6b6b696b8d7", "value": "A sitting room or lounge in a house intended mainly for use during the morning."}

{"id": "f0f0b90d-b128-4ffa-815c-1fe433b40703", "value": "Originally a room in a house where a family would gather, usually in the evening, to sit and read, write, sew, play music etc. This term has become commonly used as an alternative to living room."}
{"id": "df269bd6-0e6a-4181-baea-5dafa1f57319", "value": "A central area within a building."}
{"id": "7b324e3f-c5c3-483e-a692-46ef1ba7c3a0", "value": "A communal wash area, sometimes a dedicated outbuilding, or facility, such as a basin or trough, used by monks."}
{"id": "68032838-2700-4f34-a979-abb828614917", "value": "A path or area for exercise, usually taken in the form of walking. Can be partially or totally covered."}

{"id": "2774091b-4039-4875-ac1c-f11a59787fe6", "value": "Manmade feature to contain water for the purpose of floating miniature boats in it. Different to BOATING LAKE as lake can be naturally occuring park feature and can be used for full sized boats."}
{"id": "c63b0390-4c74-439d-b285-7c0021df9c98", "value": "A space usually in front of a church entrance but can include the space surrounding a church."}
{"id": "d900f4f2-5cdf-463c-aedd-3fd07e4718d5", "value": "A passageway or corridor beteen two areas which is covered."}
{"id": "44f60645-1281-4c97-88c0-a92b93634a0b", "value": "An enclosed area, often surrounded by walls or buildings."}
{"id": "729a9820-8324-4138-9539-e7e7abbc6ce0", "value": "An open roofed structure on which climbing plants are grown in order to provide a shaded walkway or seating area."}
{"id": "cc52eeb1-0de6-4512-87a4-cb19deb48c79", "value": "A space or area that is outside a building."}
{"id": "cb157494-131e-4792-87ef-756fbd2f81fa", "value": "An atrium or open court, surrounded by porticoes, at the west end of a church."}
{"id": "51c5e983-f1e7-45aa-8d49-080a0f3c3431", "value": "A yard intended for the purpose of taking exercise, for example within the grounds of a prison."}
{"id": "85d952d9-6182-46e4-9001-dba9377a4a14", "value": "Defences or an external wall surrounding a castle's motte or keep. Also a castle's outer court, or a court within a castle's walls."}
{"id": "ef32a93d-fa58-4750-b20d-f574d2c1da6f", "value": "A court in front of a church, usually open."}
{"id": "13f08e87-32b2-46fc-90e2-3fb909b088eb", "value": "Man made shallow pool, usually made for children to play in rather than swim."}
{"id": "a3b95456-3d15-4398-b2ec-141781e99736", "value": "A purlin that passes a principal rafter"}
{"id": "b0daa0d4-dc32-4533-943e-c33db1b500d3", "value": "A purlin that rests against the lower surface of a principal rafter and is supported by a queen post, collar or raking strut."}
{"id": "581dc96d-5de8-40a9-95e7-a31e60c9259e", "value": "A purlin that is joined to the back of a principal rafter."}
{"id": "f747ae47-c5d3-4f4c-badf-1b2e55052b92", "value": "A purlin that is threaded through a hole in the principal rafter."}
{"id": "2746513e-0211-4e66-91f3-c368af260f72", "value": "The equivalent of a colonnade but using pilasters."}
{"id": "6e48e7aa-d87d-4da8-8392-94293bc07cf2", "value": "A horizontal, stationary steam engine with two cylinders in line, one behind the other, the steam passing through each cylinder in turn."}
{"id": "cb133956-8ddd-4f77-9b87-0a587fa8ace6", "value": "Decorative ornamentation consisting of alternating bead shapes with small, elliptical forms resembling reels"}
{"id": "8973fc39-fbaa-4050-be6e-65c66bc47364", "value": "A slope, usually with rails, along which a vehicle can be moved between two relatively flat stretches of railway."}

{"id": "84f6ad8f-d0d0-4428-a13c-2b19b221b44a", "value": "A classical order having a bell shaped capital that is decorated with laurel, olive or acanthus leaves from which CAULICOLI emerge. The shaft is usually fluted and the base is often an Attic base."}
{"id": "02b79a18-b561-45df-8608-9a14e9bac7f8", "value": "A style of construction following an established set of criteria, based around the conventional use of a type of column."}
{"id": "3639a4bb-7ae3-4603-855c-f0a7b11ca1b7", "value": "A classical order in which the columns or pilasters are applied to a wall."}
{"id": "1f4b8386-264f-4522-a82d-f70cae421af7", "value": "A classical order with an Attic base and fluted column. The cornice has dentils and the capital volutes."}

{"id": "6cde3a4a-404e-4af2-a695-f002b4d908cd", "value": "A classical order with metopes and triglyphs in the frieze. Greek Doric has no base and a fluted column but Roman Doric does have a base and may or may not have a fluted column."}
{"id": "c021542d-aa9f-44f6-a934-a11cf44b4b49", "value": "An order in which the columns rise more than one storey in height from the ground or plinth."}
{"id": "82658946-da13-48a9-a826-4420345465cf", "value": "An order composed of elements of the Ionic and Corinthian orders."}

{"id": "a1238a13-228c-479f-8b7a-b98a4a7ea9c3", "value": "A room in the house of a Justice of the Peace in which cases were heard. Houses after 1848 contained these for prestige purposes since the practice of hearing cases at home was made illegal at that date."}
{"id": "08b165e9-c30c-4466-adbc-b0ac259e8003", "value": "A capital at the corner of a colonade or portico in the Ionic Order in which the volutes are splayed outwards at 45 degrees."}

{"id": "aadf9a26-408f-4211-903d-d271e83f9b57", "value": "A steam engine in which the spent steam leaving the cylinder passes to a condenser instead of being exhausted to the atmosphere. The condenser creates a partial vacuum which increases the pressure drop across the engine, so raising its efficiency."}

{"id": "223af98a-d42f-4da5-97f0-6203cd43a017", "value": "This is the top term for the class. This class includes terms with very broad definitions which could be assigned to three or more classes. See UNASSIGNED Class List for narrow terms."}
{"id": "8e3dafa3-65ed-4547-855c-f61be9ca4bcd", "value": "An archaeological unit of soil in a horizontal plane which may seal features or be cut through by other features."}
{"id": "9775e74a-ba12-4bd1-b6c6-fddf9eb12ca9", "value": "The pit in which human or animal remains are placed for interment,which may be either an inhumation or cremation."}
{"id": "142a0706-4950-43ed-8055-981f0a29c9ed", "value": "An archaeological component which cuts, overlies or abuts other features such as ditches, pits and building foundations."}
{"id": "12b0e805-2868-4f09-a7a8-32dce29e957c", "value": "A spandrel that is sunk below the surface of the arch."}
{"id": "13abdbff-0069-40a3-84d2-add112dc0e17", "value": "A small chamber or private room."}
{"id": "d73e595b-b200-4d8b-86be-ed6328cb55b3", "value": "A pilaster without base or capital."}

{"id": "a9d4941e-ce06-4897-95e6-a6284dd83600", "value": "The junction of two timbers at right angles, with chamfers or mouldings meeting on a diagonal line, where one timber is cut to fit around the chamfer or moulding of the other timber."}
{"id": "20581d6c-9e4f-4216-bda3-791b7881069a", "value": "A column that is equidistant, with intercolumniations, even at the corners, with two or more triglyphs over each intercolumniation."}
{"id": "62f7fba2-85a2-40ee-8d15-4f25061bb413", "value": "A mechanical device, used in a corn mill, that separates bran from meal to produce a whiter flour."}
{"id": "ee293048-7891-48be-a438-a9d9e221821f", "value": "A rib placed at an angle to support timbers."}
{"id": "1a1f9864-9aaf-4e9e-b0f3-85df6d9c67db", "value": "A small private chapel in either a house or church."}
{"id": "bcf97965-6fa4-43bf-93c8-de9172bd32d0", "value": "A narrow means of access, often internal."}
{"id": "deef6677-072d-4017-95ec-2f9a0add7d9c", "value": "An apartment or suite of rooms usually occupying the top floor of a building."}
{"id": "518bad16-2978-4eb7-8fe7-967ac316c49a", "value": "An area in a church, sometimes defined by screens, containing a shrine. Also a shrine, usually portable, containing religious relics."}
{"id": "08cb0e53-4e0d-40d8-822a-094d4c5d4639", "value": "An area or wing of a hexagonal plan workhouse or prison from where the supervision of the inmates is carried out."}
{"id": "3701596d-ca7a-4b38-a793-1f1f526e05c7", "value": "An area normally below a stage or dais occupied by an orchestra or musical group for performances and entertainment."}
{"id": "1fa2b448-55c1-4d6b-a0ce-becef97608de", "value": "A room in which public or private auctions are held."}
{"id": "99f823c5-090f-40c3-b711-d2c21e4227fc", "value": "One of a building's horizontal divisions, being the space between two floors, or a floor and the roof structure."}
{"id": "b96cd88b-5d66-4b24-bcbe-5201d115a780", "value": "An open area within an exchange building (e.g. cotton exchange, corn exchange, stock exchange) where goods are traded."}

{"id": "a2e2b091-a0fc-4fde-aaa4-85fce5afe473", "value": "A large division of a building which lies across, and at right angles to, its main axis, such as the arms either side of the crossing in a cruciform church."}

{"id": "1c2e9985-16a8-4098-9aa2-05936b0e2933", "value": "A roofed structure, open on one side, usually attached to a building, providing a seating area and its occupants with an uninterrupted exterior view."}
{"id": "80ead256-2219-4014-b915-f47365e56c4e", "value": "A passageway within a building providing access to rooms."}
{"id": "adb2d83b-687c-4ace-9833-2fc2e91fd65d", "value": "The body of a church or chapel as opposed to galleries."}
{"id": "838447ed-a7d6-49a9-b7c0-461580104a99", "value": "A clear area in a church covered by the transepts and crossing."}
{"id": "f208338a-36cd-40b8-81fa-a770f578700e", "value": "The area where the act of Offertory, where bread and wine are placed upon the altar, takes place."}
{"id": "b3135b8e-3457-4793-9084-5830ca9ec279", "value": "The choir and sanctuary in the liturgical eastern part of a church appropriated for those who officiate during services."}
{"id": "8059bd12-3b1c-43e6-8a6c-1046385ef2d1", "value": "The central division of a church, extending from the west end to the chancel or transepts."}
{"id": "16753f20-55b4-4ac0-adfe-cf20b0bb9b83", "value": "The partially enclosed western part of a chapel, leading to the chapel proper."}
{"id": "13a9727c-c471-427d-b11f-fbc383c07b39", "value": "A heated room within a monastery where monks could warm themselves."}
{"id": "32952026-c13d-4763-9cce-a6c33ece13ac", "value": "The space between the high altar and the east wall or chapel in a large church, and often the area west of a Monks' choir."}
{"id": "3e77f43c-8514-4ded-9730-9f72abdc7a0c", "value": "A part of the chancel of a church where the altar is situated."}
{"id": "e5c1065a-3984-4829-81ce-7fca0dbbdc91", "value": "Part of a church in front of the choir and usually enclosed by tombs, screens etc."}
{"id": "41e188f0-02d5-4263-981d-7e6bdee6726b", "value": "A building, or part of a church, used for baptismal rites, usually containing a font."}
{"id": "3d2362dd-a187-44b4-88d9-d5ab9107b2b3", "value": "An area or space within a building."}
{"id": "9702b078-3617-43b0-be01-8fb31b235b98", "value": "The part of the chancel, between the altar rail and the eastern wall, containing the high altar."}
{"id": "c6409eda-9c29-4c63-bbf7-3253b2b09630", "value": "An underground, or partially underground, vault or crypt beneath a church or other building."}
{"id": "17e51c6d-e9ba-43de-843a-ebdcc398a965", "value": "The area of the Basilica, especially in the early church, in which the altar resides."}
{"id": "5bfef2b1-9f4c-4862-966a-6b335c65f3df", "value": "Found in early churches this was a part of a church on the south side of the chancel where there were bookshelves and storage for vestments."}

{"id": "60bf42a0-078f-4863-819b-986338569867", "value": "Manmade structure that contains water that is heated to a high temperature and sometimes has bubbling air jets. Meant to be used for therapeudic purposes."}
{"id": "f8adbedc-acfa-4cb7-b1df-486a3296b356", "value": "A small dome on top of a larger dome, roof etc."}
{"id": "ca77c8bb-bd1e-45ac-a935-14e364819278", "value": "A piece of wood of square or rectangular section driven through a scarf joint to tighten it"}
{"id": "7be219ff-0024-4263-b19a-6aec94258a7f", "value": "A large room within a school or college used and appropriately furnished for the sitting of examinations by students.."}
{"id": "c15cfe5a-0dc2-4f50-b39d-8a74ad7f7800", "value": "A large communal room within a college complex used for functions, assemblies, examinations etc."}

{"id": "8e1b457c-0a71-473f-a484-4e2c45d410db", "value": "A roof with one side longer than the other, continuing at the same pitch over an extension to a building. Commonly found in New England Colonial architecture."}
{"id": "773024ea-ccda-4c5c-b9ab-31c6adc77727", "value": "A room where a committee meets to discuss matters put before them."}

{"id": "90e6003b-a123-460f-b1fe-70bd8bbd701c", "value": "A flour milling machine which uses one or more pairs of horizontal millstones to grind wheat into flour which millers call a \u2018sudden death\u2019 process; within not more than 90 seconds complete wheat grain becomes wholemeal flour."}
{"id": "03fed2c8-2783-4eff-8e12-13f6ab5d1b1b", "value": "A collective term embracing a church tower's entire structure, including its spire."}
{"id": "08df9ccf-a57b-49ce-9ec8-804f452d8bf8", "value": "A steeple in which the spire resembles a crown."}
{"id": "1f60aaf9-727e-4b0a-9c16-4a1ae553d4de", "value": "An opening normally in a door or window filled with diagonally set slats to provide ventilation."}
{"id": "fb8c7eda-1774-4f98-ad40-b8d831a7d38b", "value": "A base embellished with horizontal reeds and other mouldings."}
{"id": "d4785883-ddf9-497d-b619-f0151c7b1bbb", "value": "A room containing a toilet, water closet etc.."}
{"id": "f181f3b6-8aed-4867-a2d1-192f248f8535", "value": "A staircase divided into two parallel flights joined by a landing with no well between the outer strings."}
{"id": "a579f35f-1421-4bfd-8e5b-b3344ace5893", "value": "A beam the end of which is fixed beyond the upright it passes through."}
{"id": "5cb95a6e-69e3-4821-9f9d-20e11fea5b7b", "value": "A walkway around the parapets of a castle or the roof of a church."}
{"id": "119cdb0e-6a73-4e2b-bc99-361d3748a36e", "value": "A frieze that has a convex section."}
{"id": "20655bff-a266-44d9-b7a0-f2f025034490", "value": "The middle section, between the architrave and the cornice, of an entablature."}
{"id": "83489be3-648d-4a1a-8010-588d76e7f98c", "value": "A thin, rectangular panel, sometimes enriched with sculptural relief, placed between the triglyphs in a Doric Order frieze."}
{"id": "f4c2435a-026f-49b3-aa3c-22b5c6dd984e", "value": "A hydraulic machine used to drive a pillar crane."}
{"id": "23d685c6-da59-4221-bc81-cc390cc8dff0", "value": "A crane using hydraulic power."}
{"id": "722b7f21-0eeb-4562-8c3d-f49d4c342541", "value": "A box crane which uses hydraulic power"}
{"id": "bdfabcbd-79de-4fe2-8e41-616d3e4e22e9", "value": "A staircase, circular in plan, that winds around a central newel."}
{"id": "08ce3140-c1a7-4aa9-a4af-96f5a02cee86", "value": "The horizontal timber running the length of a roof and positioned at its apex."}
